112:## STEP 1.3 — parse args (0_parse_and_validate)
113:
114:Parse `$ARGUMENTS`: phase_number, flags (--skip-deploy, --regression-only,
115:--smoke-only, --fix-only, --skip-flow, --allow-missing-console-check,
116:--override-reason).
117:
118:Validate:
119:- `${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json` exists
120:- `${PHASE_DIR}/GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md` exists
121:- `${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md` exists
122:- `${PHASE_DIR}/API-CONTRACTS.md` exists
123:
124:Missing → BLOCK with guidance: "Run `/vg:review {phase}` first."
125:
126:**Forbidden-without-override enforcement (A5):**
127:
128:The flags listed in `forbidden_without_override` (test.md runtime_contract)
129:MUST be paired with `--override-reason "<≥50 chars>"`. Each accepted skip
130:flag emits a canonical `override.used` event via `vg-orchestrator override`
131:so the override-debt register has a stable record. Lone `--override-reason`
132:(no companion skip flag) is also gated and emits its own `override.used`
133:event tagged with `flag=--override-reason` — that way the contract drift
134:called out in review-v2 A5 can never silently swallow a justification.
135:
136:```bash
137:# Detect any forbidden skip/allow flags present in $ARGUMENTS.
138:# --override-reason itself is also in forbidden_without_override (test.md)
139:# but is handled separately below so we can attribute the override event.
140:FORBIDDEN_FLAGS=(--skip-deploy --skip-flow --allow-missing-console-check)
141:USED_FORBIDDEN=()
142:for FF in "${FORBIDDEN_FLAGS[@]}"; do
143:  if [[ " ${ARGUMENTS} " =~ [[:space:]]${FF}([[:space:]=]|$) ]]; then
144:    USED_FORBIDDEN+=("$FF")
145:  fi
146:done
147:
148:HAS_OVERRIDE_REASON=false
149:if [[ " ${ARGUMENTS} " =~ [[:space:]]--override-reason([[:space:]=]) ]]; then
150:  HAS_OVERRIDE_REASON=true
151:fi
152:
153:# Extract reason text once (vg-orchestrator validates ≥50 chars + non-placeholder).
154:OVR_REASON=""
155:if [ "$HAS_OVERRIDE_REASON" = "true" ]; then
156:  OVR_REASON=$(echo "$ARGUMENTS" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "
157:import re, sys
158:arg = sys.stdin.read()
159:m = re.search(r'--override-reason[ =](?:\"([^\"]+)\"|(\S.*))', arg)
160:if m:
161:    print((m.group(1) or m.group(2) or '').strip())
162:")
163:fi
164:
165:if [ ${#USED_FORBIDDEN[@]} -gt 0 ]; then
166:  if [ "$HAS_OVERRIDE_REASON" != "true" ]; then
167:    echo "⛔ Forbidden flag(s) used without --override-reason:"
168:    for FF in "${USED_FORBIDDEN[@]}"; do echo "   ${FF}"; done
169:    echo ""
170:    echo "Re-run with: --override-reason \"<≥50 char justification>\""
171:    exit 1
172:  fi
173:
174:  for FF in "${USED_FORBIDDEN[@]}"; do
175:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" .claude/scripts/vg-orchestrator override \
176:      --flag "$FF" --reason "$OVR_REASON" || {
177:        echo "⛔ vg-orchestrator override rejected $FF (reason too short / placeholder)."
178:        exit 1
179:      }
180:  done
181:elif [ "$HAS_OVERRIDE_REASON" = "true" ]; then
182:  # Lone --override-reason (no skip/allow companion). The flag is still
183:  # in forbidden_without_override so it MUST emit a canonical override.used
184:  # event — otherwise the parser+contract drift detected by review-v2 A5
185:  # remains: telemetry would never see the justification.
186:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" .claude/scripts/vg-orchestrator override \
187:    --flag "--override-reason" --reason "$OVR_REASON" || {
188:      echo "⛔ vg-orchestrator override rejected --override-reason (reason too short / placeholder)."
189:      exit 1
190:    }
191:fi
192:```
193:
194:**NOT_SCANNED rejection gate (tightened 2026-04-17 — GLOBAL rule):**
195:
196:Test replays `goal_sequences[]` that review wrote into RUNTIME-MAP. Goals with
197:status `NOT_SCANNED`/`FAILED` (intermediate) have no sequence → test has no
198:input → MUST NOT defer to test.
199:
200:```bash
201:vg-orchestrator step-active 0_parse_and_validate
202:
203:# Parse GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md → check for intermediate statuses
204:INTERMEDIATE=$(${PYTHON_BIN} - <<PY 2>/dev/null
205:import re, sys
206:from pathlib import Path
