111:**Future phases auto-consume:** At the start of every review (Phase 2, before discovery), read KNOWN-ISSUES.json → filter issues where `suggested_phase` matches current phase OR `affects_views` overlaps with views being reviewed → display to AI as "known issues to verify/fix in this phase".
112:
113:### 3c: Fix + Ripple Check + Redeploy
114:
115:**🎯 3-tier fix routing (tightened 2026-04-17 — cost + context isolation):**
116:
117:Sau khi bug classified ở 3a/3b (MINOR/MODERATE/MAJOR + size metadata), route tới model phù hợp theo config. Main model KHÔNG tự fix mọi thứ — MODERATE phải spawn để isolate context và save main-model tokens.
118:
119:**Config (pure user-side, workflow không giả định model vendor/tier):**
120:
121:```yaml
122:# vg.config.md
123:models:
124:  # Existing keys: planner, executor, debugger
125:  review_fix_inline: <model-id>    # model cho MINOR inline (thường = main/planner tier)
126:  review_fix_spawn:  <model-id>    # model cheaper cho MODERATE + MINOR-big-scope
127:
128:review:
129:  fix_routing:
130:    minor:
131:      inline_when:
132:        max_files: <int>
133:        max_loc_estimate: <int>
134:      else: "spawn"                # route to models.review_fix_spawn
135:    moderate:
136:      action: "spawn"              # always route to models.review_fix_spawn
137:      parallel: <bool>
138:      max_concurrent: <int>
139:    major:
140:      action: "escalate"           # REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md, không auto-fix
141:    tripwire:
142:      minor_bloat_loc: <int>
143:      action: "warn|rollback"
144:```
145:
146:Workflow CHỈ đọc model id từ `config.models.review_fix_inline` / `review_fix_spawn`. Không hardcode tên vendor (Claude/GPT/Gemini), tier (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku, o3/gpt-4o), hay capability.
147:
148:Thiếu config → fallback: inline = main model hiện tại, spawn = cùng model (degraded — không có cost optimization nhưng vẫn có context isolation).
149:
150:**Algorithm per CODE BUG:**
151:
152:```
153:1. Load severity từ error classification (step 3b)
154:2. Estimate fix scope trước khi fix:
155:   - files_to_touch = heuristic từ error location + related callers
156:   - loc_estimate = peek file around error line, count context
157:3. Route theo severity:
158:```
159:
160:**MINOR + small scope → inline (fast path, main model):**
161:```
162:If severity == MINOR AND files <= config.review.fix_routing.minor.inline_when.max_files
163:                   AND loc_estimate <= config.review.fix_routing.minor.inline_when.max_loc_estimate:
164:  Main model reads file + edits inline (current behavior)
165:  narrate_fix "[inline] MINOR ${bug_title} (${files} files, ~${loc} LOC)"
166:```
167:
168:**MINOR big scope OR MODERATE → spawn (config-driven model):**
169:
170:**Runtime branching (v2.65.0 A6) — Claude vs Codex spawn primitives:**
171:
172:Fix-agent spawn site is dual-path: Claude Code uses the native `Agent` tool;
173:Codex (`VG_RUNTIME=codex`) does NOT have the `Agent` tool, so it MUST shell
174:out to `codex-spawn.sh --tier executor` (write access required because fixes
175:edit code). See `codex-skills/vg-build/SKILL.md` "Codex spawn precedence"
176:table — `/vg:review` fix agents map to `--tier executor` with
177:`workspace-write` sandbox.
178:
179:```bash
180:SPAWN_MODEL="${config.models.review_fix_spawn:-${config.models.executor}}"
181:PROMPT_FILE="${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-prompt-${ERR_ID:-$idx}.md"
182:# (Render the structured prompt below into $PROMPT_FILE before spawning.)
183:
184:if [ "${VG_RUNTIME:-claude}" = "codex" ]; then
185:  # Codex path (v2.65.0 A6) — no Agent tool; use codex-spawn.sh executor tier.
186:  # Sandbox=workspace-write because fix-agents edit code/tests.
187:  set +e
188:  bash commands/vg/_shared/lib/codex-spawn.sh \
189:       --tier executor \
190:       --task "fix-${ERR_ID:-$idx}" \
191:       --sandbox workspace-write \
192:       --prompt-file "${PROMPT_FILE}" \
193:       --out "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-out-${ERR_ID:-$idx}.json"
194:  CODEX_FIX_RC=$?
195:  set -e
196:  if [ "$CODEX_FIX_RC" -ne 0 ]; then
197:    echo "⚠ codex-spawn fix-agent failed for ${ERR_ID:-$idx} (rc=${CODEX_FIX_RC}) — see CODEX-FIX-FAILURES.json + escalating to REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md" >&2
198:    # Persist failure record to phase dir
199:    ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} - <<PYEOF
200:import json
201:from pathlib import Path
202:from datetime import datetime, timezone
203:p = Path("${PHASE_DIR}/CODEX-FIX-FAILURES.json")
204:data = json.loads(p.read_text(encoding="utf-8")) if p.is_file() else {"failures": []}
205:data.setdefault("failures", []).append({
206:    "err_id": "${ERR_ID:-unknown}",
207:    "rc": ${CODEX_FIX_RC},
208:    "ts": datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ"),
209:    "attempt": ${TOTAL_ITER:-0},
210:})
211:p.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2), encoding="utf-8")
212:PYEOF
213:    # Emit event
214:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator" emit-event "test.codex_fix_failed" \
215:      --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"err_id\":\"${ERR_ID:-unknown}\",\"rc\":${CODEX_FIX_RC},\"attempt\":${TOTAL_ITER:-0}}" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
216:  fi
217:else
218:  # Claude path — preserve existing Agent tool spawn (narrate first, then call).
219:  bash scripts/vg-narrate-spawn.sh general-purpose spawning "fix-${ERR_ID:-$idx}" 2>/dev/null || true
220:  # Then invoke the Agent tool with the prompt body below; model/$SPAWN_MODEL
221:  # is passed as the model parameter (provider-native).
222:fi
223:```
224:
225:Prompt body (rendered into `${PROMPT_FILE}` for Codex, or passed inline to
226:the `Agent(...)` tool call on Claude):
227:
228:```
229:Agent(
230:  model="$SPAWN_MODEL",
231:  description="[fix ${idx}/${total}] ${severity} ${file}:${line} — ${bug_type}"
232:):
233:  prompt = """
234:  Fix this reviewed bug. Focused scope — no tangent changes.
235:
236:  ## BUG
237:  Severity: ${severity}
238:  Observed: ${error_description}
239:  Expected: ${expected_behavior}
240:  View: ${view_url}
241:  File hint: ${suspected_file}
242:  Evidence: ${console_errors}, ${network_failures}, ${screenshot}
243:
244:  ## CONSTRAINTS
245:  - Touch only files related to this bug
246:  - No refactor/rename unless required for fix
247:  - Write test if missing (project convention)
248:  - Commit: fix(${phase}): ${short description}
249:  - Per CONTEXT.md D-XX OR Covers goal: G-XX in commit body
250:
251:  ## RETURN
252:  - Files changed (list)
253:  - LOC delta
254:  - One-line summary
255:  """
256:
257:narrate_fix "[spawn:${SPAWN_MODEL}] ${severity} ${bug_title}"
258:```
259:
260:**MAJOR → escalate (no auto-fix):**
261:```
262:Append to REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md:
263:| bug_id | view | severity | description | why_escalated |
264:
265:narrate_fix "[escalated] MAJOR ${bug_title} → REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md"
266:```
267:
268:**Parallel spawning:**
269:
270:Nếu `config.review.fix_routing.moderate.parallel: true` và có >1 MODERATE bugs độc lập (no shared files):
271:- Group bugs by affected file → spawn Sonnet parallel per group
272:- Max `config.review.fix_routing.moderate.max_concurrent` at once
273:- Wait all → aggregate commits
274:
275:**Post-fix tripwire (catch misclassification):**
276:
277:```bash
278:TRIPWIRE_LOC="${config.review.fix_routing.tripwire.minor_bloat_loc:-0}"
279:TRIPWIRE_ACTION="${config.review.fix_routing.tripwire.action:-warn}"
280:
281:if [ "$TRIPWIRE_LOC" -gt 0 ]; then
282:  # Check each MINOR-routed-inline fix
283:  for commit in $MINOR_INLINE_COMMITS; do
284:    ACTUAL_LOC=$(git show --stat "$commit" | tail -1 | grep -oE '[0-9]+ insertion' | grep -oE '^[0-9]+')
285:    if [ "${ACTUAL_LOC:-0}" -gt "$TRIPWIRE_LOC" ]; then
286:      case "$TRIPWIRE_ACTION" in
287:        rollback)
288:          echo "⛔ MINOR inline fix bloated ($ACTUAL_LOC > $TRIPWIRE_LOC LOC) — rolling back, re-route Sonnet"
289:          git reset --hard "${commit}^"
290:          # Re-queue bug với severity upgrade → MODERATE → spawn Sonnet
291:          ;;
292:        warn|*)
293:          echo "⚠ MINOR fix ($commit) bloated: $ACTUAL_LOC LOC > $TRIPWIRE_LOC threshold. Consider re-classify."
294:          echo "tripwire: $commit actual_loc=$ACTUAL_LOC severity=MINOR" >> "${PHASE_DIR}/build-state.log"
295:          ;;
296:      esac
297:    fi
298:  done
299:fi
300:```
301:
302:**Narration format:**
303:
304:```
305:  ▶ Fix 1/5: [inline] MINOR edit button label mismatch
306:       ✓ Fixed 1 file, 2 LOC
307:
308:  ▶ Fix 2/5: [spawn] MODERATE form validation missing on /sites/new
309:       ✓ Agent completed: 3 files, 24 LOC  (model: ${SPAWN_MODEL})
310:
311:  ▶ Fix 3/5: [escalated] MAJOR bulk import UI absent
312:       → REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md
313:
314:  ▶ Fix 4/5: [inline] MINOR CSS overflow on mobile
315:       ⚠ Tripwire hit: 45 LOC > 15 threshold — flagged for re-classify
316:```
317:
318:Narrator chỉ hiển thị model id user đã config, KHÔNG hardcode "Sonnet"/"GPT-4o"/etc.
319:
320:**Then for each fixed bug (inline OR via Sonnet):**
321:
322:1. Read the relevant source file
323:2. Fix the issue
324:3. **Ripple check (graphify-powered, if active):**
325:   ```bash
326:   if [ "$GRAPHIFY_ACTIVE" = "true" ]; then
327:     # Get files changed by this fix
328:     FIXED_FILES=$(git diff --name-only HEAD)
329:     echo "$FIXED_FILES" > "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple-input.txt"
330:
331:     # Run ripple analysis on fixed files
332:     ${PYTHON_BIN} ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/build-caller-graph.py \
333:       --changed-files-input "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple-input.txt" \
334:       --config .claude/vg.config.md \
335:       --graphify-graph "$GRAPHIFY_GRAPH_PATH" \
336:       --output "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple.json"
337:
338:     # Check if fix affects callers outside the fixed file
339:     RIPPLE_COUNT=$(${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
340:     import json
341:     d = json.load(open('${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple.json'))
342:     callers = d.get('affected_callers', [])
343:     print(len(callers))
344:     ")
345:
346:     if [ "$RIPPLE_COUNT" -gt 0 ]; then
347:       echo "⚠ Fix ripple: ${RIPPLE_COUNT} callers may be affected by this change"
348:       echo "  Adding caller views to re-verify list (step 3d)"
349:       # Map caller files → views for re-verification in step 3d
350:       RIPPLE_VIEWS=$(${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
351:       import json
352:       d = json.load(open('${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple.json'))
353:       for c in d.get('affected_callers', []):
354:         print(c)
355:       ")
356:     fi
357:   fi
358:   ```
359:   Without graphify: step 3d re-verifies affected views by git diff only (may miss indirect callers).
360:4. Commit with message: `fix({phase}): {description}`
361:
362:After all fixes:
363:```
364:Redeploy using env-commands.md deploy(env)
365:Health check → if fail → rollback
366:```
367:
368:### 3d: Re-verify (Sonnet parallel — focused on fixed zones)
369:
370:After fix+redeploy, spawn Sonnet agents to re-verify affected views + ripple zones:
371:
372:```
373:1. Get new SHA: git rev-parse HEAD
374:2. git diff old_sha..new_sha → list changed files
375:3. Map changed files to views (using code_patterns from config):
376:   - Changed API routes → views that call those endpoints
377:   - Changed page components → those specific views
378:   - Graphify ripple callers (from step 3c) → views importing those callers
379:4. Group affected views + ripple views into zones
380:
381:5. Spawn Sonnet agents (parallel) for affected zones ONLY:
382:   Agent prompt: "Re-verify these fixed actions in {zone}.
383:     Previous errors: {error list from 3a}
384:     Expected: errors should be resolved.
385:     Test each previously-failed action.
386:     Also check: did the fix break anything else on this view?
387:     Report: {action, was_broken, now_works, new_issues}"
388:
389:6. Wait all → merge results:
390:   - Fixed errors → update matrix: ❌ → 🔍 REVIEW-PASSED
391:   - Still broken → keep ❌, increment iteration
392:   - New errors from fix → add to error list
393:   - Update RUNTIME-MAP with corrected observations
394:   - Log current build SHA in PIPELINE-STATE.json `steps.review.last_fix_sha`
395:```
396:
397:### 3d.5: QA-Checker meta-verification (v2.68.0 C2, hardened v2.69.0)
398:
399:**v2.69.0 T3 escape hatch:** `SKIP_QA_CHECK=1` short-circuits this step
400:(set by parse loop when `--skip-qa-check` is passed; logs override-debt).
401:When unset, full QA-Checker spawn runs.
402:
403:After Phase 3 fix-loop converges (verdict=ok or max_iter reached), spawn QA-Checker
404:to verify each fix commit ACTUALLY addresses the original review finding it was
405:meant to fix — not just makes tests pass. Detects suppression hacks, false fixes,
406:and test reverts.
407:
408:```bash
409:if [ "${SKIP_QA_CHECK:-0}" = "1" ]; then
410:  echo "▸ Phase 3d.5: --skip-qa-check set (debt-tracked); skipping QA-Checker meta-verification" >&2
411:  mkdir -p "${PHASE_DIR}/.step-markers" 2>/dev/null
412:  touch "${PHASE_DIR}/.step-markers/phase3d_5_qa_checker.done"
413:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator mark-step review phase3d_5_qa_checker 2>/dev/null || true
414:else
415:  bash scripts/vg-narrate-spawn.sh vg-review-qa-checker spawning "QA-check ${PHASE_NUMBER} fix commits"
416:  # Then: Agent(subagent_type="vg-review-qa-checker",
417:  #             prompt=<rendered with phase_dir + fix_commits list>)
418:fi
419:```
420:
421:Marker: `phase3d_5_qa_checker` (v2.69.0:
422:`required_unless_flag: --skip-qa-check` — hard-block flipped from
423:v2.68.0 advisory severity=warn).
424:
425:The QA-Checker returns PASS|PARTIAL|FAIL per fix and a cumulative verdict.
426:On PARTIAL/FAIL (v2.69.0 onward), review BLOCKs unless
427:`--skip-qa-check --override-reason=<text>` was passed. Operators must
428:either fix the underlying issue, route to /vg:amend, or log debt via the
429:escape hatch.
430:
431:### 3e: Iterate
432:
433:Repeat 3a-3d until:
434:- RUNTIME-MAP is **stable** (no new errors between 2 iterations)
435:- Zero CODE BUG errors remaining
436:- `MAX_ITER=5` iterations reached (v2.65.0 A4 bump from 3 → 5 for multi-class buckets)
437:
438:**Per-iteration telemetry (v2.65.0 A4):** at the top of every iteration body, emit
439:`review.fix_iteration_started` so operators can watch progress mid-loop:
440:
441:```bash
442:# Emit at the start of each iteration (after ITER + VIOLATION_COUNT are known).
443:"${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
444:  "review.fix_iteration_started" --actor "review" --outcome "INFO" \
445:  --metadata "{\"iter\":${ITER},\"max_iter\":${MAX_ITER:-5},\"violations\":${VIOLATION_COUNT:-0}}" \
446:  >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
447:```
448:
449:Display after each iteration:
450:```
451:Fix iteration {N}/${MAX_ITER:-5}:
452:  Errors fixed: {N}
453:  Errors remaining: {N} (infra: {N}, spec-gap: {N}, pre-existing: {N})
454:  Sonnet agents spawned: {N} (re-verified {M} views)
455:  New errors found: {N}
456:  Matrix coverage: {review_passed}/{total} goals
457:  Map stable: {YES|NO}
458:```
459:
460:### 3e: Iter limit fallback — Diagnostic L2 (RFC v9 D11 + D26, PR-E)
461:
462:When the final iteration (`ITER == MAX_ITER`, default 5) exits with errors STILL
463:remaining (loop hit cap without self-resolving), do NOT silent-BLOCK. Spawn
464:diagnostic_l2 single-advisory fallback:
465:
466:1. Capture residual evidence: list of unresolved error rows from
467:   RUNTIME-MAP + scan-*.json + recipe_executor logs.
468:2. Spawn isolated Haiku subagent (zero parent context — RFC v9 D11) to
469:   classify root cause `block_family` ∈ {schema_drift, validation_bug,
470:   auth_issue, db_constraint, business_logic, integration_failure,
471:   unknown}.
472:3. L2 generates `L2Proposal.json` with confidence + proposed_fix.
473:4. Present to user via single-advisory pattern (D26):
474:     - confidence ≥ 0.7  → "Đề xuất: <fix>. [Yes / chi tiết]"
475:     - confidence < 0.7  → 3-option block_resolve_l3_present (legacy)
476:5. **User gate is mandatory** — never auto-apply (per project policy).
477:6. User accept → apply fix → re-run one extra iteration grace (ITER+1).
478:7. User reject → BLOCK with full audit trail in
479:   `.l2-proposals/{proposal_id}.json` + DEFECT-LOG entry referencing
480:   the proposal.
481:
482:```bash
483:if [ "${ITER:-1}" -eq "${MAX_ITER:-5}" ] && [ -n "${REMAINING_ERRORS}" ] && \
484:   { [ -f "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py" ] || [ -f "${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py" ]; }; then
485:  echo "━━━ Phase 3e — Diagnostic L2 fallback (iter ${ITER} hit cap=${MAX_ITER:-5}) ━━━"
486:  DIAGNOSTIC_L2="${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py"
487:  [ -f "$DIAGNOSTIC_L2" ] || DIAGNOSTIC_L2="${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py"
488:  L2_ARGS=(
489:    --phase "${PHASE_NUMBER}"
490:    --gate-id "review.fix_loop"
491:    --evidence-file "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-loop-evidence.json"
492:  )
493:  L2_OUT=$("${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "$DIAGNOSTIC_L2" \
494:    "${L2_ARGS[@]}" 2>&1)
495:  L2_PROPOSAL_ID=$(echo "$L2_OUT" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "
496:import json, sys
497:try: print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('proposal_id',''))
498:except: print('')
499:")
500:  if [ -n "$L2_PROPOSAL_ID" ]; then
501:    echo "  L2 proposal generated: $L2_PROPOSAL_ID"
502:    # Open DEFECT-LOG entry referencing the proposal
503:    TESTER_PRO_CLI="${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/tester-pro-cli.py"
504:    [ -f "$TESTER_PRO_CLI" ] || TESTER_PRO_CLI="${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/tester-pro-cli.py"
505:    if [ -f "$TESTER_PRO_CLI" ]; then
506:      "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "$TESTER_PRO_CLI" defect new \
507:        --phase "${PHASE_NUMBER}" \
508:        --title "[ITER-LIMIT] Fix loop hit max=${MAX_ITER:-5}, L2 proposal $L2_PROPOSAL_ID" \
509:        --severity major --found-in review \
510:        --notes "L2 proposal at .l2-proposals/${L2_PROPOSAL_ID}.json — user decision pending" \
511:        2>&1 | sed 's/^/  /' || true
512:    fi
513:    # User gate is provider-native after spawn-diagnostic-l2.py:
514:    # Claude Code uses AskUserQuestion; Codex asks in the main thread/UI.
515:    # On accept → run-complete sees applied; on reject → BLOCK below.
516:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
517:      "review.diagnostic_l2_spawned" \
518:      --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"proposal_id\":\"$L2_PROPOSAL_ID\"}" \
519:      >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
520:  fi
521:fi
522:```
523:
524:> **Tại sao không tự apply L2 fix**: L2 đã sai trong dogfood 3.2
525:> (propose fix giả mà có vẻ hợp lý). User gate là single source of truth
526:> cho fix correctness. Audit trail (`.l2-proposals/`) cho phép trace
527:> sau-incident: proposal nào được accept/reject, fix tham chiếu commit nào.
528:</step>
529:
530:<step name="step7_matrix_verdict" mode="full">
531:## Step 7: MATRIX VERDICT (post-fix-loop)
532:
533:→ `narrate_phase "Phase 7 — Goal comparison" "So khớp ${N} goals từ TEST-GOALS với views đã khám phá"`
534:
535:```bash
536:"${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator step-active step7_matrix_verdict >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
537:```
538:
539:### 4.0: RCRURD runtime verification (Task 23 — Codex GPT-5.5 review 2026-05-03)
540:
541:For every TEST-GOALS/G-NN.md with `goal_type: mutation`, run the runtime
542:gate. BLOCK review on assertion fail (R8 update_did_not_apply, etc).
543:Action payload comes from per-phase fixture (`FIXTURES/G-NN.action.json`).
544:
545:```bash
546:EVIDENCE_DIR="${PHASE_DIR}/.rcrurd-evidence"
547:mkdir -p "$EVIDENCE_DIR"
548:RCRURD_FAILED=0
549:RCRURD_RAN=0
550:
551:if [ -d "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS" ]; then
552:  for goal in "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS"/G-*.md; do
553:    [ -f "$goal" ] || continue
554:    grep -qE "goal_type:[[:space:]]*mutation" "$goal" || continue
555:    RCRURD_RAN=$((RCRURD_RAN+1))
556:    ev_out="${EVIDENCE_DIR}/$(basename "$goal" .md).json"
557:
558:    payload="{}"
559:    fixture="${PHASE_DIR}/FIXTURES/$(basename "$goal" .md).action.json"
560:    [ -f "$fixture" ] && payload=$(cat "$fixture")
561:
562:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/validators/verify-rcrurd-runtime.py \
563:      --goal-file "$goal" \
564:      --phase "${PHASE_NUMBER}" \
565:      --action-payload "$payload" \
566:      --auth-header "$(vg_config_get review.rcrurd_auth_header '')" \
567:      --evidence-out "$ev_out" || RCRURD_FAILED=1
568:  done
569:fi
570:
571:if [ "$RCRURD_RAN" -gt 0 ]; then
572:  if [ "$RCRURD_FAILED" = "1" ]; then
573:    echo "⛔ Phase 4.0 RCRURD runtime — at least one mutation goal failed (of ${RCRURD_RAN} run)"
574:    echo "   Evidence: ${EVIDENCE_DIR}/*.json"
575:    echo "   Route through classifier (Task 7) — most are IN_SCOPE for current phase"
576:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
577:      "review.rcrurd_runtime_failed" \
578:      --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"evidence_dir\":\"${EVIDENCE_DIR}\",\"goals_run\":${RCRURD_RAN}}" \
579:      2>/dev/null || true
580:    exit 1
581:  fi
582:
583:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
584:    "review.rcrurd_runtime_passed" \
585:    --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"goals_run\":${RCRURD_RAN}}" \
586:    2>/dev/null || true
587:fi
588:```
589:
590:### 4a: Load Goals + edge cases
591:
592:Load goals via `vg-load --phase ${PHASE_NUMBER} --artifact goals` (generated by /vg:blueprint).
593:If missing → generate from CONTEXT.md + API-CONTRACTS.md (fallback).
594:
595:**P1 v2.49+ — Edge case variants:** also load `${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES/G-NN.md`
596:per goal. Status format extended:
597:- Old: `G-04: PASS` / `G-04: FAIL` / `G-04: NOT_TESTED`
598:- New: `G-04: PASS (5/6 variants — G-04-c1 NOT_TESTED [needs concurrency harness])`
599:
600:For each variant in EDGE-CASES/G-NN.md:
601:- Replay `start_view` (per RUNTIME-MAP) with variant's input
602:- Verify expected_outcome matches actual UI/API response
603:- Mark per-variant: PASS | FAIL | NOT_TESTED (with reason)
604:- Aggregate to goal status (goal PASS only when all critical/high variants PASS)
605:
606:Skip variants when:
607:- EDGE-CASES file missing (legacy phase pre-v2.49) → emit
608:  `review.edge_cases_unavailable` (severity=warn) + treat goal as 1-variant
609:- Variant priority=low + `--skip-low-edge-cases` flag set
610:- No-CRUD phase (CRUD-SURFACES.resources empty) → no variants expected
611:
612:Emit per gate-blocked variant: `review.edge_case_variant_blocked` with
613:`{goal_id, variant_id, reason}` payload.
614:
615:Parse goals: ID, description, success criteria, mutation evidence, dependencies, priority.
616:
617:**Post-build lifecycle contract (v3.6.7) — review MUST consume `/vg:test-spec` artifacts, not only gate their existence.**
618:
619:Load these artifacts before mapping goals:
620:- `${PHASE_DIR}/LIFECYCLE-SPECS.json` — side-effecting / multi-actor lifecycle contract per goal.
621:- `${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-FIXTURE-DAG.json` — fixture dependency graph and cleanup order.
622:- `${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-EXECUTION-PLAN.json` — runner family per phase profile (`web`, `mobile`, `backend`, `cli`, `library`, `mixed`).
623:- `${PHASE_DIR}/DEEP-TEST-SPECS.md` — human-readable provenance and gap context.
624:
625:Review uses them as the lifecycle comparison contract:
626:- Runtime blockers still produce `BLOCKED` and stay in review/debug.
627:- Missing RCRURDR lifecycle proof with clean runtime produces `TEST_PENDING`, then advances to `/vg:test`.
628:- Runner-native phases (`mobile`, `backend`, `cli`, `library`) must not be forced into Playwright/browser semantics; use `TEST-EXECUTION-PLAN.json.family`.
629:- If lifecycle artifacts name a goal that legacy `TEST-GOALS.md` parsing missed, include that goal in `GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md` so review cannot silently drop it.
630:
631:**Surface classification (v1.9.1 R1 — lazy migration, runs BEFORE browser discover decisions):**
632:
633:```bash
634:# shellcheck source=_shared/lib/goal-classifier.sh
635:. ${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/goal-classifier.sh
636:set +e
637:classify_goals_if_needed "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md" "${PHASE_DIR}"
638:gc_rc=$?
639:set -e
640:# rc=2 → provider-native cheap classifier
641:#        Claude: Haiku Task per row; Codex: read-only scanner adapter over pending TSV
642:# rc=3 → provider-native prompt (surface list from config), then classify_goals_apply
643:```
644:
645:Parse `**Surface:** <name>` per goal.
646:
647:**Surface-aware routing (tightened v1.9.1 R1):**
648:
649:For each goal:
650:- `surface == "ui"` / `"ui-mobile"` → proceed with existing browser RUNTIME-MAP lookup below.
651:- `surface ∈ { api, data, time-driven, integration, custom }` → skip browser discover for this goal; instead run lightweight **surface probe**:
652:  * `api`        → grep `apps/**/src/**` for route handler matching contract path → READY if present.
653:  * `data`       → grep migrations + `config.infra_deps` for table/collection → READY if present; INFRA_PENDING if service unavailable.
654:  * `time-driven`→ grep cron/scheduler registration in `apps/workers/**`/`apps/api/**` → READY if handler wired.
655:  * `integration`→ check `${PHASE_DIR}/test-runners/fixtures/${gid}.integration.sh` exists AND downstream caller found → READY.
656:
657:Result feeds GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX with `(status, surface, probe_evidence)`.
658:
659:**Pure-backend fast-path:**
660:```bash
661:UI_GOAL_COUNT=$(grep -c '^\*\*Surface:\*\* ui' "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md" || echo 0)
662:if [ "$UI_GOAL_COUNT" -eq 0 ]; then
663:  echo "🧭 Pure-backend phase (không có goal UI) — bỏ qua browser discovery (khám phá trình duyệt), dùng surface probes." >&2
664:  # Emit empty RUNTIME-MAP if not written yet, skip to 4b
665:  [ -f "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" ] || echo '{"views":{},"goal_sequences":{}}' > "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json"
666:  # Issue #120: runtime_contract still requires one root scan-*.json artifact
667:  # even when backend-only review legitimately skips browser discovery. Emit a
668:  # synthetic backend scan so run-complete does not false-block on must_write.
669:  BACKEND_SCAN_JSON="${PHASE_DIR}/scan-backend-surface-probes.json"
670:  if [ ! -f "$BACKEND_SCAN_JSON" ]; then
671:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" - "$BACKEND_SCAN_JSON" <<'PY'
672:import json
673:import sys
674:from datetime import datetime, timezone
675:from pathlib import Path
676:
677:payload = {
678:    "view": "backend://surface-probes",
679:    "surface": "backend",
680:    "generated_by": "step7_matrix_verdict.pure_backend_fastpath",
681:    "generated_at": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat().replace("+00:00", "Z"),
682:    "results": [],
683:    "forms": [],
684:    "tables": [],
685:    "modal_triggers": [],
686:    "sub_views_discovered": [],
687:}
688:Path(sys.argv[1]).write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2) + "\n", encoding="utf-8")
689:PY
690:  fi
691:fi
692:```
693:
694:**Mixed-phase surface probe execution (v1.9.2.3 P3):**
695:
696:For phases có CẢ UI goals (cần browser) VÀ backend goals (api/data/integration/time-driven), browser phase chỉ cover UI goals. Backend goals PHẢI được probe SEPARATELY để avoid rơi vào NOT_SCANNED branch.
697:
698:```bash
699:# Run surface probes cho goals có surface ≠ ui
700:source "${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/surface-probe.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
701:if type -t run_surface_probe >/dev/null 2>&1; then
702:  PROBE_RESULTS_JSON="${PHASE_DIR}/.surface-probe-results.json"
703:  echo '{"probed_at":"'"$(date -u +%FT%TZ)"'","results":{' > "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
704:  FIRST=true
705:
706:  # Extract goal_id + surface pairs from TEST-GOALS.md
707:  ${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
708:import re
709:tg = open('${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md', encoding='utf-8').read()
710:for gid, surface in re.findall(r'^## Goal (G-[\w]+):.*?^\*\*Surface:\*\* (\w[\w-]*)', tg, re.M|re.S):
711:    print(f'{gid} {surface}')
712:" | while read -r gid surface; do
713:    surface="${surface%$'\r'}"
714:    # Skip UI — browser phase handles them
715:    [ "$surface" = "ui" ] || [ "$surface" = "ui-mobile" ] && continue
716:
717:    PROBE=$(run_surface_probe "$gid" "$surface" "$PHASE_DIR" 2>/dev/null)
718:    STATUS=$(echo "$PROBE" | cut -d'|' -f1)
719:    EVIDENCE=$(echo "$PROBE" | cut -d'|' -f2- | sed 's/"/\\"/g')
720:
721:    [ "$FIRST" = "true" ] && FIRST=false || echo "," >> "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
722:    printf '"%s":{"surface":"%s","status":"%s","evidence":"%s"}' \
723:           "$gid" "$surface" "$STATUS" "$EVIDENCE" >> "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
724:  done
725:
726:  echo '}}' >> "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
727:
728:  # Summary narration
729:  PROBED=$(${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
730:import json
731:d = json.load(open('$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON'))['results']
732:from collections import Counter
733:c = Counter(r['status'] for r in d.values())
734:print(f'Phase 4a surface probes: {len(d)} backend goals probed → {dict(c)}')")
735:  echo "▸ $PROBED"
736:
737:  # v2.48.1 (Issue #85) — backfill synthetic goal_sequences[gid] for non-UI
738:  # goals from probe results so verify-matrix-evidence-link.py (which only
739:  # inspects RUNTIME-MAP goal_sequences[]) sees backend evidence. Closes the
740:  # surface-probe schema gap that BLOCKed Phase 3.2 dogfood with 32 non-UI
741:  # READY goals flagged matrix_status_without_runtime_sequence.
742:  # Idempotent: re-runs overwrite synthetic entries by gid, never overwrites
743:  # real browser-recorded sequences.
744:  if [ -f "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/backfill-surface-probe-runtime.py" ]; then
745:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/backfill-surface-probe-runtime.py" \
746:      --phase-dir "$PHASE_DIR" 2>&1 | sed 's/^/▸ /' || true
747:  fi
748:fi
749:```
750:
751:**Phase 4b integration:** Khi check goal_sequences cho backend goals (surface ≠ ui), trước khi mark NOT_SCANNED hãy check `.surface-probe-results.json`:
752:- Nếu probe READY → map → STATUS: READY với evidence từ probe (handler path, migration file, caller reference).
753:- Nếu probe BLOCKED → map → STATUS: BLOCKED với evidence là probe reason.
754:- Nếu probe INFRA_PENDING → map → STATUS: INFRA_PENDING.
755:- Nếu probe SKIPPED (can't parse criteria) → fallthrough to NOT_SCANNED branch → buộc user cải thiện TEST-GOALS hoặc override.
756:
757:**Lifecycle contract integration (v3.6.7):**
758:- If `LIFECYCLE-SPECS.json.goals[G-XX]` exists and runtime/probe found a real API/render/data blocker → keep `BLOCKED`.
759:- If runtime/probe is clean but RCRURDR stages, fixture DAG, actor handoff, artifact capture, or cleanup are not proven by review evidence → mark `TEST_PENDING`, not `BLOCKED`.
760:- If no browser sequence exists for a runner-native lifecycle goal (`family in {mobile, backend, cli, library}`) → mark `TEST_PENDING` with runner/family evidence from `TEST-EXECUTION-PLAN.json`.
761:- If a web lifecycle goal has no `goal_sequences[G-XX]` → keep `NOT_SCANNED`; review must still discover the route/action before `/vg:test` can generate reliable replay steps.
762:
763:**Infra dependency filter (config-driven):**
764:
765:If goal has `**Infra deps:**` field (e.g., `[clickhouse, kafka, pixel_server]`):
766:```bash
767:# Check each infra dep against current environment
768:for dep in goal.infra_deps:
769:  SERVICE_CHECK=$(read config.infra_deps.services[dep].check_${ENV})
770:  if ! eval "$SERVICE_CHECK" 2>/dev/null; then
771:    goal.status = "INFRA_PENDING"
772:    goal.skip_reason = "${dep} not available on ${ENV}"
773:  fi
774:done
775:```
776:
777:Goals classified as `INFRA_PENDING` are **excluded from gate calculation** (when `config.infra_deps.unmet_behavior == "skip"`). They don't count as BLOCKED or FAIL — they're simply not testable on current environment.
778:
779:Display: `INFRA_PENDING ({dep})` in matrix with distinct icon.
780:
781:**Console noise filter (config-driven):**
782:
783:When evaluating console errors from Phase 2 discovery, filter against `config.console_noise.patterns`:
784:```bash
785:if [ "${config_console_noise_enabled}" = "true" ]; then
786:  for pattern in config.console_noise.patterns:
787:    # Remove matching errors from bug list — classify as INFRA_NOISE
788:    REAL_ERRORS=$(echo "$ALL_CONSOLE_ERRORS" | grep -viE "$pattern")
789:  done
790:  NOISE_COUNT=$((TOTAL_ERRORS - REAL_ERROR_COUNT))
791:  echo "Console: ${REAL_ERROR_COUNT} real errors, ${NOISE_COUNT} infra noise (filtered)"
792:fi
793:```
794:
795:Only REAL_ERRORS (not matching noise patterns) count as view failures.
796:
797:### 4b: Map Goals to RUNTIME-MAP
798:
799:For each goal, check goal_sequences in RUNTIME-MAP.json:
800:
801:```
802:For each goal:
803:  IF goal_sequences[goal_id] exists AND result == "passed":
804:    → STATUS: READY (goal was verified during Pass 2a)
805:
806:  IF goal_sequences[goal_id] exists AND result == "failed":
807:    → STATUS: BLOCKED (with specific failure steps from goal_sequence)
808:
809:  IF goal_sequences[goal_id] does NOT exist:
810:    # Before marking UNREACHABLE, verify code presence to distinguish
811:    # true "not built" from "built but not scanned"
812:    code_exists = check via grep against config.code_patterns:
813:      - Does goal's expected page file exist? (e.g., FloorRulesListPage.tsx)
814:      - Is the route registered? (e.g., /floor-rules in router)
815:      - Do related API endpoints have handlers? (grep API-CONTRACTS vs apps/api/)
816:
817:    IF code_exists == FALSE:
818:      → STATUS: UNREACHABLE (feature not built — fix with /vg:build --gaps-only)
819:
820:    IF code_exists == TRUE:
821:      → STATUS: NOT_SCANNED (intermediate only — MUST resolve before review exits)
822:      Root cause likely one of:
823:        - Multi-step wizard/mutation needs dedicated browser session
824:        - Goal path not reachable from discovered sidebar (orphan route)
825:        - Review ran --retry-failed but this goal wasn't in retry set
826:        - Haiku agent timed out or skipped
827:        - Goal has no UI surface but TEST-GOALS didn't mark infra_deps
828:      → RESOLUTION (tightened 2026-04-17 — NOT_SCANNED không được defer sang /vg:test):
829:        NOT_SCANNED là trạng thái TRUNG GIAN, KHÔNG phải kết luận hợp lệ.
830:        Review PHẢI resolve thành 1 trong 4 status kết luận: READY | BLOCKED | UNREACHABLE | INFRA_PENDING
831:        Cách resolve (pick 1):
832:          a) /vg:review {phase} --retry-failed với deeper probe (nếu timeout/depth issue)
833:          b) Goal không có UI surface → update TEST-GOALS với `**Infra deps:** [<user-defined no-ui tag>]` → re-classify INFRA_PENDING (tag value do user định nghĩa trong config.infra_deps, workflow không hardcode)
834:          c) Orphan/hidden route → verify config.code_patterns.frontend_routes đã cover pattern đó
835:          d) Genuinely unreachable (feature đã build nhưng UX path không exist) → manually mark UNREACHABLE with reason note
836:```
837:
838:**Status semantics (tightened 2026-04-17):**
839:
840:4 **status kết luận hợp lệ** (chỉ 4 status này được write vào GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX final):
841:
842:| Status | Meaning | Fix command |
843:|---|---|---|
844:| READY | Goal verified, evidence in goal_sequences | none |
845:| BLOCKED | View found, scan ran, criteria failed | fix code → `--retry-failed` |
846:| UNREACHABLE | Code not in repo / UX path không exist | `/vg:build --gaps-only` |
847:| INFRA_PENDING | Goal needs service/infra not available on ENV | deploy infra or sandbox |
848:
849:2 **status trung gian** (PHẢI resolve trước khi exit Phase 4):
850:
851:| Status | Meaning | Action BẮT BUỘC |
852:|---|---|---|
853:| NOT_SCANNED | Code exists, review didn't replay | `--retry-failed` HOẶC re-classify thành 1 trong 4 status trên |
854:| FAILED | Scan timeout/exception | check logs → `--retry-failed` |
855:
856:**⛔ GLOBAL RULE: KHÔNG được defer NOT_SCANNED sang /vg:test.**
857:
858:Lý do: `/vg:test` codegen LẤY steps từ `goal_sequences[]` mà review ghi. NOT_SCANNED = review không ghi sequence = codegen không có input. Test không phải fallback cho review miss.
859:
860:Goals không có UI surface đúng ra phải mark `infra_deps: [<no-ui tag>]` trong TEST-GOALS (tag value do project config quy ước) → skip ở review (INFRA_PENDING) → test qua integration/unit layer ở build phase, KHÔNG qua /vg:test E2E.
861:
862:### 4c-pre: ⛔ NOT_SCANNED resolution gate (tightened 2026-04-17)
863:
864:Trước khi chạy weighted gate, PHẢI resolve mọi `NOT_SCANNED` + `FAILED` thành 1 trong 4 kết luận.
865:
866:```bash
867:# OHOK-8 round-4 Codex fix: replace pseudocode with real bash grep.
868:# Previously `count goals where status == "NOT_SCANNED"` was not executable
869:# → gate couldn't run → NOT_SCANNED goals slipped through unresolved.
870:MATRIX="${PHASE_DIR}/GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md"
871:NOT_SCANNED_COUNT=$(grep -cE '^\| G-[0-9]+.*\|[[:space:]]*NOT_SCANNED[[:space:]]*\|' "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)
872:FAILED_COUNT=$(grep -cE '^\| G-[0-9]+.*\|[[:space:]]*FAILED[[:space:]]*\|' "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)
873:INTERMEDIATE=$((NOT_SCANNED_COUNT + FAILED_COUNT))
874:# Build the list of intermediate goal IDs (used later in override auto-convert)
875:INTERMEDIATE_GOALS=$(grep -oE '^\| (G-[0-9]+)[^|]*\|[^|]*\|[^|]*\|[[:space:]]*(NOT_SCANNED|FAILED)[[:space:]]*\|' "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null \
876:  | grep -oE 'G-[0-9]+' | sort -u | tr '\n' ' ')
877:
878:if [ "$INTERMEDIATE" -gt 0 ]; then
879:  echo "⛔ Review cannot exit Phase 4 — ${INTERMEDIATE} intermediate goals:"
880:  echo "   NOT_SCANNED: ${NOT_SCANNED_COUNT}"
881:  echo "   FAILED:      ${FAILED_COUNT}"
882:  echo ""
883:  echo "Intermediate ≠ conclusion. Resolve before exit:"
884:  echo "  a) /vg:review ${PHASE_NUMBER} --retry-failed  (deeper probe)"
885:  echo "  b) Update TEST-GOALS with 'Infra deps: [backend_only]' nếu goal không có UI"
886:  echo "     → re-classify INFRA_PENDING"
887:  echo "  c) Fix config.code_patterns.frontend_routes nếu route ẩn khỏi sidebar"
888:  echo "  d) Manual re-classify UNREACHABLE (feature không tồn tại) với reason note"
889:  echo ""
890:  echo "⛔ KHÔNG ĐƯỢC defer sang /vg:test để 'cover' NOT_SCANNED goals."
891:  echo "   Test codegen lấy input từ goal_sequences review ghi. NOT_SCANNED = no input."
892:  echo ""
893:  echo "Override (NOT RECOMMENDED — creates debt):"
894:  echo "  /vg:review ${PHASE_NUMBER} --allow-intermediate"
895:  echo "  → Auto-convert remaining NOT_SCANNED → UNREACHABLE với reason='review-skip'"
896:  echo "  → Logged to GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md 'Debt' section"
897:
898:  if [[ ! "$ARGUMENTS" =~ --allow-intermediate ]]; then
899:    # v1.9.1 R2+R4: block-resolver — try L1 auto-fix (re-scan failed goals) before demanding user override.
900:    # If L1 fails, L2 architect proposal is presented through provider-native L3 prompt.
901:    # L4 only when L2 proposal rejected AND no user direction.
902:    # See _shared/lib/block-resolver.sh
903:    source "${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/block-resolver.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
904:    if type -t block_resolve >/dev/null 2>&1; then
905:      export VG_CURRENT_PHASE="$PHASE_NUMBER" VG_CURRENT_STEP="review.4c-pre"
906:      BR_GATE_CONTEXT="NOT_SCANNED/FAILED goals block review exit. ${INTERMEDIATE} intermediate goals need conclusion (READY/BLOCKED/UNREACHABLE/INFRA_PENDING)."
907:      BR_EVIDENCE=$(printf '{"not_scanned":%d,"failed":%d,"total_intermediate":%d}' "$NOT_SCANNED_COUNT" "$FAILED_COUNT" "$INTERMEDIATE")
908:      BR_CANDIDATES='[{"id":"retry-failed-scan","cmd":"echo retry-failed auto-fix would re-trigger scanner for FAILED goals only; skipping in safe mode","confidence":0.5,"rationale":"retry-failed probe may reclassify goals without human override"}]'
909:      BR_RESULT=$(block_resolve "not-scanned-defer" "$BR_GATE_CONTEXT" "$BR_EVIDENCE" "$PHASE_DIR" "$BR_CANDIDATES")
910:      BR_LEVEL=$(echo "$BR_RESULT" | ${PYTHON_BIN} -c "import json,sys; print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('level',''))" 2>/dev/null)
911:      if [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L1" ]; then
912:        echo "✓ Block resolver L1 self-resolved — intermediate goals auto-fixed"
913:      elif [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L2" ]; then
914:        block_resolve_l2_handoff "not-scanned-defer" "$BR_RESULT" "$PHASE_DIR"
915:        echo "  Để proceed sau khi user chấp nhận proposal: re-run /vg:review ${PHASE_NUMBER} --allow-intermediate --reason='<applied proposal>'" >&2
916:        exit 2
917:      else
918:        # L4 truly stuck — print human-direction message
919:        block_resolve_l4_stuck "not-scanned-defer" "L1 failed + L2 produced no actionable proposal"
920:        exit 1
921:      fi
922:    else
923:      exit 1
924:    fi
925:  else
926:    # v1.9.0 T1: rationalization guard — NOT_SCANNED defer is a classic rationalization surface.
927:    RATGUARD_RESULT=$(rationalization_guard_check "not-scanned-defer" \
928:      "NOT_SCANNED = review didn't replay the goal sequence. Deferring = test codegen has no input. Auto-UNREACHABLE hides coverage debt." \
929:      "intermediate_goals=${INTERMEDIATE_GOALS} not_scanned=${NOT_SCANNED_COUNT} failed=${FAILED_COUNT}")
930:    if ! rationalization_guard_dispatch "$RATGUARD_RESULT" "not-scanned-defer" "--allow-intermediate" "$PHASE_NUMBER" "review.4c-pre" "${INTERMEDIATE} intermediate goals"; then
931:      exit 1
932:    fi
933:    # OHOK-8 round-4 Codex fix: update_goal_status was undefined function.
934:    # Replaced with real bash sed that rewrites matrix row in-place.
935:    # Auto-convert intermediate → UNREACHABLE với audit trail.
936:    TS=$(date -u +%FT%TZ)
937:    for gid in $INTERMEDIATE_GOALS; do
938:      # Match row `| G-XX |...|...|...| (NOT_SCANNED|FAILED) |`, replace
939:      # status column only. Preserve other columns. Use | delimiter in sed
940:      # to avoid conflicts with pipe chars in evidence.
941:      sed -i -E "s|^(\| ${gid} \|[^|]+\|[^|]+\|[^|]+\|)[[:space:]]*(NOT_SCANNED\|FAILED)[[:space:]]*\|(.*)$|\1 UNREACHABLE |review-skip-\2 @${TS}\3|" \
942:        "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null || true
943:    done
944:    echo "intermediate-override: ${INTERMEDIATE} goals auto-converted UNREACHABLE ts=$(date -u +%FT%TZ)" \
945:      >> "${PHASE_DIR}/build-state.log"
946:  fi
947:fi
948:```
949:
950:### 4c: Write GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md (v1.9.2.4 runnable merger)
951:
952:```bash
953:# Call matrix-merger.sh helper — reads RUNTIME-MAP + probe-results + TEST-GOALS,
954:# computes per-goal status with priority precedence (browser > probe > code_exists),
955:# writes canonical GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md with summary + by-priority + details + gate.
956:source "${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/matrix-merger.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
957:if type -t merge_and_write_matrix >/dev/null 2>&1; then
958:  MERGE_OUTPUT=$(merge_and_write_matrix "$PHASE_DIR" \
959:    "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md" \
960:    "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" \
961:    "${PHASE_DIR}/.surface-probe-results.json" \
962:    "${PHASE_DIR}/GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md" 2>&1)
963:
964:  # Extract machine-readable counts + verdict
965:  VERDICT=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^VERDICT=' | cut -d= -f2)
966:  READY=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^READY=' | cut -d= -f2)
967:  BLOCKED=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^BLOCKED=' | cut -d= -f2)
968:  TEST_PENDING=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^TEST_PENDING=' | cut -d= -f2)
969:  NOT_SCANNED=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^NOT_SCANNED=' | cut -d= -f2)
970:  INTERMEDIATE=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^INTERMEDIATE=' | cut -d= -f2)
971:  export VERDICT READY BLOCKED TEST_PENDING NOT_SCANNED INTERMEDIATE
972:
973:  echo "✓ GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md: VERDICT=$VERDICT (ready=$READY blocked=$BLOCKED test_pending=$TEST_PENDING not_scanned=$NOT_SCANNED)"
974:else
975:  echo "⚠ matrix-merger.sh missing — falling back to manual matrix write (legacy path)"
976:  # Legacy path: orchestrator writes matrix directly using template below
977:fi
978:
979:# Bind GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md + RUNTIME-MAP.json provenance to both runtime
980:# evidence and post-build lifecycle artifacts. This makes run-complete catch
981:# stale matrix reuse, lifecycle-spec drift, AND stale runtime-map reuse after
982:# review. Closes #175: must_write artifacts existed on disk but had no
983:# evidence-manifest entries → manual emit-evidence-manifest calls required.
984:EMIT_MANIFEST="${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/emit-evidence-manifest.py"
985:[ -f "$EMIT_MANIFEST" ] || EMIT_MANIFEST="${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/emit-evidence-manifest.py"
986:if [ -f "$EMIT_MANIFEST" ]; then
987:  if [ -f "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" ]; then
988:    set +e
989:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "$EMIT_MANIFEST" \
990:      --path "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" \
991:      --producer "vg:review phase2b3_runtime_map" \
992:      --source-inputs "${PHASE_DIR}/nav-discovery.json,${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md"
993:    EMIT_RC=$?
994:    set -e
995:    if [ "$EMIT_RC" -ne 0 ]; then
996:      echo "⚠ manifest emit failed for RUNTIME-MAP.json (rc=${EMIT_RC})" >&2
