246:## Step C — codegen per goal (READY goals)
247:
248:For each goal in status_map, branch by status:
249:
250:| Status | Action |
251:|---|---|
252:| `READY` / `READY_BEHAVIORAL` / `READY_STRUCTURAL` (+ non-empty `goal_sequences[G-XX]`) | Generate full spec (Step C.1). |
253:| `READY*` + missing `goal_sequences[G-XX]` | **BLOCK** — emit error: "Goal G-XX READY in matrix but RUNTIME-MAP has no sequence. Re-run /vg:review --retry-failed." |
254:| `MANUAL` | Emit skeleton with `test.skip()` (Step C.2). |
255:| `DEFERRED` | Skip entirely — log `[skip-deferred] {gid}`. |
256:| `INFRA_PENDING` | Emit skeleton `.skip()` with infra comment (Step C.2). |
257:| `BLOCKED` / `UNREACHABLE` | Skip — review gate should have caught these. Log error. |
258:| `NOT_SCANNED` | **BLOCK** — review gate let this through. Emit error: "Goal G-XX NOT_SCANNED. Re-run /vg:review." |
259:
260:**Batch 34 F8: status normalization (CRITICAL).** Before routing, normalize
261:`READY_STRUCTURAL` and `READY_BEHAVIORAL` to `READY` so the existing READY
262:branch logic applies uniformly. Audit found bare `READY` was the only
263:handled case; structural/behavioral READY goals (emitted by review verdict
264:matrix) silently dropped through. Status normalization happens once after
265:loading `goal-status.json`:
266:
267:```python
268:# Batch 34 F8: normalize READY variants before branch
269:NORMALIZE = {"READY_STRUCTURAL": "READY", "READY_BEHAVIORAL": "READY"}
270:for gid, status in list(status_map.items()):
271:    status_map[gid] = NORMALIZE.get(status, status)
272:```
273:
274:Also: `NOT_SCANNED` is now BLOCKed in test-spec/codegen (was only blocked
275:in /vg:test preflight per F9 — moved upstream).
