406:## Step F — L1/L2 binding gate
407:
408:### F.1 — R7 console monitoring enforcement gate
409:
410:Verify generated mutation specs have console assertion:
411:
412:```python
413:import json, re, sys, os
414:from pathlib import Path
415:
416:# Batch 47 H: prefer CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json as canonical spec list over glob.
417:# Manifest has authoritative goal_id binding; glob may pick up stale orphans.
418:tests_dir = Path("${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}")
419:manifest_path = Path("${PHASE_DIR}/CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json")
420:spec_files = []
421:if manifest_path.is_file():
422:    try:
423:        m = json.loads(manifest_path.read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
424:        entries = m.get("playwright_specs") or m.get("specs") or []
425:        for e in entries:
426:            p = e.get("path") if isinstance(e, dict) else str(e)
427:            if not p:
428:                continue
429:            cand = Path(p) if Path(p).is_absolute() else Path.cwd() / p
430:            if cand.is_file():
431:                spec_files.append(cand)
432:    except Exception:
433:        spec_files = []
434:if not spec_files:
435:    # Fallback: glob (legacy phase or manifest absent)
436:    spec_files = list(tests_dir.rglob("*.spec.ts"))
437:
438:SETUP_PATTERNS = [
439:    r'window\.__consoleErrors',
440:    r'page\.on\s*\(\s*[\'"]console[\'"]',
441:    r'captureConsoleErrors',
442:]
443:ASSERT_PATTERNS = [
444:    r'expect\s*\(\s*(?:errs|consoleErrors|window\.__consoleErrors)[\[\.\w]*\s*\)\.toBe\s*\(\s*0\s*\)',
445:    r'expect\s*\(\s*.*console.*\)\.toBe(?:Less|Equal)',
446:]
447:MUTATION_PATTERNS = [
448:    r'(?:POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE)\s+',
449:    r'waitForResponse.*(?:post|put|patch|delete)',
450:]
451:
452:violations = []
453:for spec in spec_files:
454:    content = spec.read_text(encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore')
455:    has_mutation = any(re.search(p, content, re.IGNORECASE) for p in MUTATION_PATTERNS)
456:    has_assert = any(re.search(p, content) for p in ASSERT_PATTERNS)
457:    if has_mutation and not has_assert:
458:        violations.append(spec.name)
459:
460:if violations:
461:    # BLOCK — emit in l2_escalations if block-resolver fails
462:    pass
463:```
464:
465:Override: `--allow-missing-console-check` (logs override-debt).
