522:### F.3 — goal-test binding gate (verify-goal-test-binding.py)
523:
524:After R7 gate and adversarial gate, run the binding verification:
525:
526:```bash
527:GTB_MODE=$(vg_config_get build_gates.goal_test_binding_phase_end strict)
528:if [ "$GTB_MODE" != "off" ]; then
529:  PHASE_FIRST_COMMIT=$(git log --format="%H" --reverse --grep="${PHASE_NUMBER}-" | head -1)
530:  SCAN_TAG="${PHASE_FIRST_COMMIT:+${PHASE_FIRST_COMMIT}^}"
531:  SCAN_TAG="${SCAN_TAG:-HEAD~200}"
532:
533:  GTB_ARGS="--phase-dir ${PHASE_DIR} --wave-tag ${SCAN_TAG} --wave-number phase-end"
534:  [ "$GTB_MODE" = "warn" ] && GTB_ARGS="${GTB_ARGS} --lenient"
535:
536:  if ! ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} .claude/scripts/verify-goal-test-binding.py ${GTB_ARGS}; then
537:    echo "⛔ Goal-test binding FAILED."
538:
539:    # Attempt L1 via block-resolver (re-codegen candidate)
540:    source "${REPO_ROOT}/.claude/commands/vg/_shared/lib/block-resolver.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
541:    if type -t block_resolve >/dev/null 2>&1; then
542:      export VG_CURRENT_PHASE="${PHASE_NUMBER}" VG_CURRENT_STEP="test.5b-goal-test-binding"
543:      BR_GATE_CTX="Goal-test binding gate: plan tasks claim goals but no corresponding test file found."
544:      BR_EVIDENCE=$(printf '{"gate":"goal_test_binding_phase_end","generated_tests_dir":"%s","mode":"%s"}' "$GENERATED_TESTS_DIR" "$GTB_MODE")
545:      BR_CANDIDATES='[{"id":"recodegen","cmd":"echo L1-SAFE: would invoke codegen-only rerun; exit 1","confidence":0.6,"rationale":"codegen drift is most common cause"}]'
546:      BR_RESULT=$(block_resolve "goal-test-binding" "$BR_GATE_CTX" "$BR_EVIDENCE" "$PHASE_DIR" "$BR_CANDIDATES")
547:      BR_LEVEL=$(echo "$BR_RESULT" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "import json,sys; print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('level',''))" 2>/dev/null)
548:      if [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L1" ]; then
549:        echo "✓ L1 resolved — re-run verification"
550:        ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} .claude/scripts/verify-goal-test-binding.py ${GTB_ARGS}
551:        L1_RESOLVED=$((L1_RESOLVED + 1))
552:      elif [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L2" ]; then
553:        # L2: package architect proposal for return JSON l2_escalations
554:        block_resolve_l2_handoff "goal-test-binding" "$BR_RESULT" "$PHASE_DIR"
555:        L2_ITEMS+=("goal-test-binding|$(echo "$BR_RESULT" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "import json,sys; print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('architect_proposal',''))" 2>/dev/null)|binding gate failed")
556:      else
557:        block_resolve_l4_stuck "goal-test-binding" "L1 re-codegen failed, L2 architect unavailable"
558:        BINDING_FAILED=true
559:      fi
560:    else
561:      BINDING_FAILED=true
562:    fi
563:  fi
564:fi
565:```
566:
567:**L1/L2 binding gate summary:**
568:
569:| Outcome | Behavior |
570:|---|---|
571:| Binding passes | Continue to return JSON. |
572:| L1 self-resolved | `l1_resolved_count` incremented; re-verify passes. |
573:| L2 needed | Package `architect_proposal` text into `l2_escalations`; main agent handles via `AskUserQuestion`. |
574:| L4 stuck | Binding FAILED recorded; main agent sees `binding_failed: true`. |
575:
576:The `5d_binding_gate` step is NOT marked at orchestrator level — it is
577:subagent-internal. The binding gate's `verify-goal-test-binding.py` call
578:and the block-resolver L1/L2 loop are both fully contained here.
