1:#!/usr/bin/env python3
2:"""B62 (audit ID-3): verify every CRUD resource has feature_chain goal.
3:
4:CRUD-SURFACES.md (Batch 33) lists CRUD endpoints per resource. For each
5:resource with a CREATE endpoint (POST), TEST-GOALS.md MUST contain ≥1
6:goal with `goal_class: feature_chain` AND:
7:
8:  - chain_steps length ≥ 8 (anti-cheat threshold from audit ID-3)
9:  - distinct `expected_state` per step
10:  - at least 1 step where `target_view_class` is NOT in
11:    {source_view, source_view_modal, source_view_form} — chain MUST
12:    traverse to a structurally different view
13:  - at least 2 steps with non-empty `downstream_effects[]` — chain
14:    MUST observe downstream consequences, not just rename existing
15:    shallow mutation steps
16:
17:OR the resource has explicit `feature_chain_waiver: <reason>` in
18:CONTEXT.md (declared per-resource).
19:
20:This validator BLOCKS the blueprint gate when CRUD resources lack
21:feature_chain goals.
22:
23:Usage:
24:  verify-feature-chain-coverage.py --phase 7
25:  verify-feature-chain-coverage.py --phase 7 --strict
26:  verify-feature-chain-coverage.py --phase 7 --allow-feature-chain-shortfall
