57:<LANGUAGE_POLICY>
58:Follow `_shared/language-policy.md`. Default narration is Vietnamese; file
59:paths, command names, JSON keys, and code identifiers stay English.
60:</LANGUAGE_POLICY>
61:
62:<objective>
63:Run the dedicated deep test-spec lane after `/vg:build` and before
64:`/vg:review`.
65:
66:Why this exists:
67:- Blueprint is too early: implemented DOM, route files, API handlers, generated
68:  UI, and concrete form state may not exist yet.
69:- Build must not self-certify runtime coverage.
70:- Review should verify runtime against a pre-authored deep spec contract, not
71:  discover test depth late and route it ambiguously.
72:
73:Pipeline:
74:`specs → scope → blueprint → build → review → test-spec → test → accept`
75:</objective>
76:
77:<rules>
78:1. This command is post-build only. Missing `SUMMARY*.md`, `BUILD-LOG.md`, or
79:   `.build-progress.json` BLOCKs with guidance to run `/vg:build`.
80:2. It authors test-depth contracts, not executable test specs. Executable
81:   specs still belong to `/vg:test`.
82:3. Mutation and multi-actor goals must get closed-loop RCRURDR coverage:
83:   read_before → create → read_after_create → update → read_after_update →
84:   delete → read_after_delete.
85:4. Fixture dependencies must be explicit: actors, sessions, resource ownership,
86:   artifact sinks, cleanup order.
87:5. VG is profile-aware. Web may use Playwright, mobile may use Maestro/Appium/native,
88:   CLI may use command assertions, backend may use HTTP/RPC/job checks, library may
89:   use unit/property tests.
90:6. Review consumes these artifacts. If review finds runtime blockers, stay in
91:   review/debug. If runtime is clean but executable specs are missing, route to
92:   `/vg:test`.
93:</rules>
