649:<step name="4_codegen">
650:
651:## Step 4: codegen (`4_codegen`)
652:
653:Spawn `vg-test-codegen` subagent to generate Playwright lifecycle specs per goal. Smart-routing applies lens set per `goal_type` from `GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.json`.
654:
655:**Smart-routing lens map:**
656:
657:| `goal_type` | Lens set |
658:|---|---|
659:| `mutation` | `idor` + `mass-assignment` + `authz-negative` + `business-logic` |
660:| `read` | `authz` + `info-disclosure` + `tenant-boundary` |
661:| `auth` | `auth-jwt` + `csrf` + `duplicate-submit` |
662:| `default` | `business-coherence` + `input-injection` |
663:
664:**Subagent invocation:**
665:
666:Read `commands/vg/_shared/test/codegen/delegation.md` and `commands/vg/_shared/test/codegen/overview.md` (existing files, no change). Then:
667:
668:```
669:Agent(
670:  subagent_type="vg-test-codegen",
671:  prompt=<from delegation.md template>,
672:  input={
673:    phase_dir: "${PHASE_DIR}",
674:    phase_number: "${PHASE_NUMBER}",
675:    phase_profile: "${PHASE_PROFILE}",
676:    runtime_map_path: "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json",
677:    goal_coverage_matrix_path: "${PHASE_DIR}/GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.json",
678:    generated_tests_dir: "tests/e2e/lifecycle/",
679:    lens_routing_map: <smart-routing map above>
680:  }
681:)
682:```
683:
684:**Output contract:**
685:- `tests/e2e/lifecycle/G-XX.{lens}.spec.ts` — one file per goal × lens
686:- `${PHASE_DIR}/CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json` — list of generated files + their L1/L2 binding state
687:
688:**Post-spawn gate (F1 Batch 19):**
689:
690:```bash
691:# F1 Batch 19: vg-test-codegen MUST write CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json + playwright
692:# spec files. Marker gates on those outputs (mirrors Batch 15 F3/F4 pattern).
693:CODEGEN_MANIFEST="${PHASE_DIR}/CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json"
694:if [ ! -f "$CODEGEN_MANIFEST" ]; then
695:  echo "⛔ F1 BLOCK: vg-test-codegen did not write CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json" >&2
696:  echo "   Codegen Agent spawn produced no output. Re-run /vg:test-spec ${PHASE_NUMBER}." >&2
697:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" .claude/scripts/vg-orchestrator emit-event "test_spec.codegen_missing_manifest" \
698:    --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\"}" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
699:  exit 1
700:fi
701:# Spec count check — manifest must list playwright specs
702:SPEC_COUNT=$("${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" -c "
703:import json
704:m = json.loads(open('${CODEGEN_MANIFEST}', encoding='utf-8').read())
705:specs = m.get('playwright_specs', m.get('specs', []))
706:print(len(specs))
707:" 2>/dev/null || echo "0")
708:if [ "${SPEC_COUNT:-0}" -lt 1 ]; then
709:  echo "⛔ F1 BLOCK: CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json contains 0 playwright specs" >&2
710:  echo "   vg-test-codegen claims to have run but produced no spec files." >&2
711:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" .claude/scripts/vg-orchestrator emit-event "test_spec.codegen_zero_specs" \
712:    --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\"}" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
713:  exit 1
714:fi
715:echo "✓ F1: codegen wrote ${SPEC_COUNT} playwright specs"
716:```
