1878:23:
1879:24:### 3a: Error Summary
1880:25:
1881:26:Collect errors from ALL sources:
1882:27:- RUNTIME-MAP.json: `errors[]` array + per-view `issues[]` + failed `goal_sequences` + `free_exploration` issues
1883:28:- `${PHASE_DIR}/REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md` (if exists — written by /vg:test when MODERATE/MAJOR issues found):
1884:29:  Parse issues table → add to error list with severity from test classification
1885:30:  These are issues test couldn't fix — review MUST address them in this fix loop
1886:31:- `${PLANNING_DIR}/KNOWN-ISSUES.json`: issues matching current phase/views (already loaded at init)
1887:32:
1888:33:### 3b: Classify Errors
1889:34:
1890:35:For each error:
1891:36:- **CODE BUG** → fix immediately (wrong logic, missing validation, UI mismatch)
1892:37:- **INFRA ISSUE** → escalate to user (service unavailable, config wrong)
1893:38:- **SPEC GAP** → record in SPEC-GAPS.md (see 3b-spec-gaps) — feature not built, decision missing from CONTEXT/PLAN
1894:39:- **PRE-EXISTING** → don't fix, write to `${PLANNING_DIR}/KNOWN-ISSUES.json` (see below)
1895:40:
1896:41:### 3b-spec-gaps: Feed SPEC_GAPS back to blueprint (fixes G9)
1897:42:
1898:43:When ≥3 SPEC_GAP errors accumulate, or any critical-priority goal maps to SPEC_GAP, emit `${PHASE_DIR}/SPEC-GAPS.md` and surface to user with a concrete re-plan command:
1899:44:
1900:45:```markdown
1901:46:# Spec Gaps — Phase {phase}
1902:47:
1903:48:Detected during /vg:review phase 3b. Listed issues trace to missing CONTEXT decisions or un-tasked PLAN items — not code bugs. Review cannot fix these; blueprint must re-plan.
1904:49:
1905:50:## Gaps
1906:51:| # | Observed Issue | Related Goal | Likely Missing | Source Evidence |
1907:52:|---|----------------|--------------|----------------|-----------------|
1908:53:| 1 | Site delete has no confirmation modal | G-08 (delete site) | D-XX: "delete requires confirmation" decision | screenshot {phase}-sites-delete-error.png |
1909:54:| 2 | Bulk import UI absent | G-12 (bulk import) | Task for CSV upload handler + FE form | grep "bulk" in code returns 0 matches |
1910:55:...
1911:56:
1912:57:## Recommended action
1913:58:
1914:59:This is NOT a code bug. Re-run blueprint in patch mode to append tasks covering these gaps:
1915:60:
1916:61:    /vg:blueprint {phase} --from=2a
1917:62:
1918:63:This spawns planner with the gap list as input. Existing tasks preserved; missing ones appended. Then re-run build → review.
1919:64:
1920:65:Do NOT attempt to fix these in the review fix loop — the fix loop targets code bugs, not missing scope.
1921:66:```
1922:67:
1923:68:Threshold + auto-suggestion:
1924:69:```bash
1925:70:SPEC_GAP_COUNT=$(count of SPEC_GAP-classified errors)
1926:71:CRITICAL_SPEC_GAPS=$(count where related goal is priority:critical)
1927:72:
1928:73:if [ $SPEC_GAP_COUNT -ge 3 ] || [ $CRITICAL_SPEC_GAPS -ge 1 ]; then
1929:74:  echo "⚠ ${SPEC_GAP_COUNT} spec gaps detected (${CRITICAL_SPEC_GAPS} critical)."
1930:75:  echo "See: ${PHASE_DIR}/SPEC-GAPS.md"
1931:76:  echo ""
1932:77:  echo "This is a planning gap, not a code bug. Recommended:"
1933:78:  echo "   /vg:blueprint ${PHASE} --from=2a   (re-plan with gap feedback)"
1934:79:  echo ""
1935:80:  echo "Review fix loop will continue for code bugs only; spec gaps stay open until blueprint re-run."
1936:81:fi
1937:82:```
