1967:112:
1968:113:### 3c: Fix + Ripple Check + Redeploy
1969:114:
1970:115:**🎯 3-tier fix routing (tightened 2026-04-17 — cost + context isolation):**
1971:116:
1972:117:Sau khi bug classified ở 3a/3b (MINOR/MODERATE/MAJOR + size metadata), route tới model phù hợp theo config. Main model KHÔNG tự fix mọi thứ — MODERATE phải spawn để isolate context và save main-model tokens.
1973:118:
1974:119:**Config (pure user-side, workflow không giả định model vendor/tier):**
1975:120:
1976:121:```yaml
1977:122:# vg.config.md
1978:123:models:
1979:124:  # Existing keys: planner, executor, debugger
1980:125:  review_fix_inline: <model-id>    # model cho MINOR inline (thường = main/planner tier)
1981:126:  review_fix_spawn:  <model-id>    # model cheaper cho MODERATE + MINOR-big-scope
1982:127:
1983:128:review:
1984:129:  fix_routing:
1985:130:    minor:
1986:131:      inline_when:
1987:132:        max_files: <int>
1988:133:        max_loc_estimate: <int>
1989:134:      else: "spawn"                # route to models.review_fix_spawn
1990:135:    moderate:
1991:136:      action: "spawn"              # always route to models.review_fix_spawn
1992:137:      parallel: <bool>
1993:138:      max_concurrent: <int>
1994:139:    major:
1995:140:      action: "escalate"           # REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md, không auto-fix
1996:141:    tripwire:
1997:142:      minor_bloat_loc: <int>
1998:143:      action: "warn|rollback"
1999:144:```
2000:145:
2001:146:Workflow CHỈ đọc model id từ `config.models.review_fix_inline` / `review_fix_spawn`. Không hardcode tên vendor (Claude/GPT/Gemini), tier (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku, o3/gpt-4o), hay capability.
2002:147:
2003:148:Thiếu config → fallback: inline = main model hiện tại, spawn = cùng model (degraded — không có cost optimization nhưng vẫn có context isolation).
2004:149:
2005:150:**Algorithm per CODE BUG:**
2006:151:
2007:152:```
2008:153:1. Load severity từ error classification (step 3b)
2009:154:2. Estimate fix scope trước khi fix:
2010:155:   - files_to_touch = heuristic từ error location + related callers
2011:156:   - loc_estimate = peek file around error line, count context
2012:157:3. Route theo severity:
2013:158:```
2014:159:
2015:160:**MINOR + small scope → inline (fast path, main model):**
2016:161:```
2017:162:If severity == MINOR AND files <= config.review.fix_routing.minor.inline_when.max_files
2018:163:                   AND loc_estimate <= config.review.fix_routing.minor.inline_when.max_loc_estimate:
2019:164:  Main model reads file + edits inline (current behavior)
2020:165:  narrate_fix "[inline] MINOR ${bug_title} (${files} files, ~${loc} LOC)"
2021:166:```
2022:167:
2023:168:**MINOR big scope OR MODERATE → spawn (config-driven model):**
2024:169:
2025:170:**Runtime branching (v2.65.0 A6) — Claude vs Codex spawn primitives:**
2026:171:
2027:172:Fix-agent spawn site is dual-path: Claude Code uses the native `Agent` tool;
2028:173:Codex (`VG_RUNTIME=codex`) does NOT have the `Agent` tool, so it MUST shell
2029:174:out to `codex-spawn.sh --tier executor` (write access required because fixes
2030:175:edit code). See `codex-skills/vg-build/SKILL.md` "Codex spawn precedence"
2031:176:table — `/vg:review` fix agents map to `--tier executor` with
2032:177:`workspace-write` sandbox.
2033:178:
2034:179:```bash
2035:180:SPAWN_MODEL="${config.models.review_fix_spawn:-${config.models.executor}}"
2036:181:PROMPT_FILE="${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-prompt-${ERR_ID:-$idx}.md"
2037:182:# (Render the structured prompt below into $PROMPT_FILE before spawning.)
