2113:258:```
2114:259:
2115:260:**MAJOR → escalate (no auto-fix):**
2116:261:```
2117:262:Append to REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md:
2118:263:| bug_id | view | severity | description | why_escalated |
2119:264:
2120:265:narrate_fix "[escalated] MAJOR ${bug_title} → REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md"
2121:266:```
2122:267:
2123:268:**Parallel spawning:**
2124:269:
2125:270:Nếu `config.review.fix_routing.moderate.parallel: true` và có >1 MODERATE bugs độc lập (no shared files):
2126:271:- Group bugs by affected file → spawn Sonnet parallel per group
2127:272:- Max `config.review.fix_routing.moderate.max_concurrent` at once
2128:273:- Wait all → aggregate commits
2129:274:
2130:275:**Post-fix tripwire (catch misclassification):**
2131:276:
2132:277:```bash
2133:278:TRIPWIRE_LOC="${config.review.fix_routing.tripwire.minor_bloat_loc:-0}"
2134:279:TRIPWIRE_ACTION="${config.review.fix_routing.tripwire.action:-warn}"
2135:280:
2136:281:if [ "$TRIPWIRE_LOC" -gt 0 ]; then
2137:282:  # Check each MINOR-routed-inline fix
2138:283:  for commit in $MINOR_INLINE_COMMITS; do
2139:284:    ACTUAL_LOC=$(git show --stat "$commit" | tail -1 | grep -oE '[0-9]+ insertion' | grep -oE '^[0-9]+')
2140:285:    if [ "${ACTUAL_LOC:-0}" -gt "$TRIPWIRE_LOC" ]; then
2141:286:      case "$TRIPWIRE_ACTION" in
2142:287:        rollback)
2143:288:          echo "⛔ MINOR inline fix bloated ($ACTUAL_LOC > $TRIPWIRE_LOC LOC) — rolling back, re-route Sonnet"
2144:289:          git reset --hard "${commit}^"
2145:290:          # Re-queue bug với severity upgrade → MODERATE → spawn Sonnet
2146:291:          ;;
2147:292:        warn|*)
2148:293:          echo "⚠ MINOR fix ($commit) bloated: $ACTUAL_LOC LOC > $TRIPWIRE_LOC threshold. Consider re-classify."
2149:294:          echo "tripwire: $commit actual_loc=$ACTUAL_LOC severity=MINOR" >> "${PHASE_DIR}/build-state.log"
2150:295:          ;;
2151:296:      esac
2152:297:    fi
2153:298:  done
2154:299:fi
2155:300:```
2156:301:
2157:302:**Narration format:**
2158:303:
2159:304:```
2160:305:  ▶ Fix 1/5: [inline] MINOR edit button label mismatch
2161:306:       ✓ Fixed 1 file, 2 LOC
2162:307:
2163:308:  ▶ Fix 2/5: [spawn] MODERATE form validation missing on /sites/new
2164:309:       ✓ Agent completed: 3 files, 24 LOC  (model: ${SPAWN_MODEL})
2165:310:
2166:311:  ▶ Fix 3/5: [escalated] MAJOR bulk import UI absent
2167:312:       → REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md
2168:313:
2169:314:  ▶ Fix 4/5: [inline] MINOR CSS overflow on mobile
2170:315:       ⚠ Tripwire hit: 45 LOC > 15 threshold — flagged for re-classify
2171:316:```
2172:317:
2173:318:Narrator chỉ hiển thị model id user đã config, KHÔNG hardcode "Sonnet"/"GPT-4o"/etc.
2174:319:
2175:320:**Then for each fixed bug (inline OR via Sonnet):**
2176:321:
2177:322:1. Read the relevant source file
2178:323:2. Fix the issue
2179:324:3. **Ripple check (graphify-powered, if active):**
2180:325:   ```bash
2181:326:   if [ "$GRAPHIFY_ACTIVE" = "true" ]; then
2182:327:     # Get files changed by this fix
2183:328:     FIXED_FILES=$(git diff --name-only HEAD)
2184:329:     echo "$FIXED_FILES" > "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple-input.txt"
2185:330:
2186:331:     # Run ripple analysis on fixed files
2187:332:     ${PYTHON_BIN} ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/build-caller-graph.py \
2188:333:       --changed-files-input "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple-input.txt" \
2189:334:       --config .claude/vg.config.md \
2190:335:       --graphify-graph "$GRAPHIFY_GRAPH_PATH" \
2191:336:       --output "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple.json"
2192:337:
2193:338:     # Check if fix affects callers outside the fixed file
2194:339:     RIPPLE_COUNT=$(${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
2195:340:     import json
2196:341:     d = json.load(open('${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple.json'))
2197:342:     callers = d.get('affected_callers', [])
2198:343:     print(len(callers))
2199:344:     ")
2200:345:
2201:346:     if [ "$RIPPLE_COUNT" -gt 0 ]; then
2202:347:       echo "⚠ Fix ripple: ${RIPPLE_COUNT} callers may be affected by this change"
2203:348:       echo "  Adding caller views to re-verify list (step 3d)"
2204:349:       # Map caller files → views for re-verification in step 3d
2205:350:       RIPPLE_VIEWS=$(${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
2206:351:       import json
2207:352:       d = json.load(open('${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-ripple.json'))
2208:353:       for c in d.get('affected_callers', []):
2209:354:         print(c)
2210:355:       ")
2211:356:     fi
2212:357:   fi
2213:358:   ```
2214:359:   Without graphify: step 3d re-verifies affected views by git diff only (may miss indirect callers).
2215:360:4. Commit with message: `fix({phase}): {description}`
2216:361:
2217:362:After all fixes:
2218:363:```
2219:364:Redeploy using env-commands.md deploy(env)
2220:365:Health check → if fail → rollback
2221:366:```
2222:367:
2223:368:### 3d: Re-verify (Sonnet parallel — focused on fixed zones)
2224:369:
2225:370:After fix+redeploy, spawn Sonnet agents to re-verify affected views + ripple zones:
2226:371:
2227:372:```
2228:373:1. Get new SHA: git rev-parse HEAD
2229:374:2. git diff old_sha..new_sha → list changed files
2230:375:3. Map changed files to views (using code_patterns from config):
2231:376:   - Changed API routes → views that call those endpoints
2232:377:   - Changed page components → those specific views
2233:378:   - Graphify ripple callers (from step 3c) → views importing those callers
2234:379:4. Group affected views + ripple views into zones
2235:380:
2236:381:5. Spawn Sonnet agents (parallel) for affected zones ONLY:
2237:382:   Agent prompt: "Re-verify these fixed actions in {zone}.
2238:383:     Previous errors: {error list from 3a}
2239:384:     Expected: errors should be resolved.
2240:385:     Test each previously-failed action.
2241:386:     Also check: did the fix break anything else on this view?
2242:387:     Report: {action, was_broken, now_works, new_issues}"
2243:388:
2244:389:6. Wait all → merge results:
2245:390:   - Fixed errors → update matrix: ❌ → 🔍 REVIEW-PASSED
2246:391:   - Still broken → keep ❌, increment iteration
2247:392:   - New errors from fix → add to error list
2248:393:   - Update RUNTIME-MAP with corrected observations
2249:394:   - Log current build SHA in PIPELINE-STATE.json `steps.review.last_fix_sha`
2250:395:```
2251:396:
2252:397:### 3d.5: QA-Checker meta-verification (v2.68.0 C2, hardened v2.69.0)
2253:398:
2254:399:**v2.69.0 T3 escape hatch:** `SKIP_QA_CHECK=1` short-circuits this step
2255:400:(set by parse loop when `--skip-qa-check` is passed; logs override-debt).
2256:401:When unset, full QA-Checker spawn runs.
2257:402:
2258:403:After Phase 3 fix-loop converges (verdict=ok or max_iter reached), spawn QA-Checker
2259:404:to verify each fix commit ACTUALLY addresses the original review finding it was
2260:405:meant to fix — not just makes tests pass. Detects suppression hacks, false fixes,
2261:406:and test reverts.
2262:407:
2263:408:```bash
2264:409:if [ "${SKIP_QA_CHECK:-0}" = "1" ]; then
2265:410:  echo "▸ Phase 3d.5: --skip-qa-check set (debt-tracked); skipping QA-Checker meta-verification" >&2
2266:411:  mkdir -p "${PHASE_DIR}/.step-markers" 2>/dev/null
2267:412:  touch "${PHASE_DIR}/.step-markers/phase3d_5_qa_checker.done"
2268:413:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator mark-step review phase3d_5_qa_checker 2>/dev/null || true
2269:414:else
2270:415:  bash scripts/vg-narrate-spawn.sh vg-review-qa-checker spawning "QA-check ${PHASE_NUMBER} fix commits"
2271:416:  # Then: Agent(subagent_type="vg-review-qa-checker",
2272:417:  #             prompt=<rendered with phase_dir + fix_commits list>)
2273:418:fi
2274:419:```
2275:420:
2276:421:Marker: `phase3d_5_qa_checker` (v2.69.0:
2277:422:`required_unless_flag: --skip-qa-check` — hard-block flipped from
2278:423:v2.68.0 advisory severity=warn).
2279:424:
2280:425:The QA-Checker returns PASS|PARTIAL|FAIL per fix and a cumulative verdict.
2281:426:On PARTIAL/FAIL (v2.69.0 onward), review BLOCKs unless
2282:427:`--skip-qa-check --override-reason=<text>` was passed. Operators must
2283:428:either fix the underlying issue, route to /vg:amend, or log debt via the
2284:429:escape hatch.
2285:430:
2286:431:### 3e: Iterate
2287:432:
2288:433:Repeat 3a-3d until:
2289:434:- RUNTIME-MAP is **stable** (no new errors between 2 iterations)
2290:435:- Zero CODE BUG errors remaining
2291:436:- `MAX_ITER=5` iterations reached (v2.65.0 A4 bump from 3 → 5 for multi-class buckets)
2292:437:
2293:438:**Per-iteration telemetry (v2.65.0 A4):** at the top of every iteration body, emit
2294:439:`review.fix_iteration_started` so operators can watch progress mid-loop:
2295:440:
2296:441:```bash
2297:442:# Emit at the start of each iteration (after ITER + VIOLATION_COUNT are known).
2298:443:"${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
2299:444:  "review.fix_iteration_started" --actor "review" --outcome "INFO" \
2300:445:  --metadata "{\"iter\":${ITER},\"max_iter\":${MAX_ITER:-5},\"violations\":${VIOLATION_COUNT:-0}}" \
2301:446:  >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
2302:447:```
2303:448:
2304:449:Display after each iteration:
2305:450:```
2306:451:Fix iteration {N}/${MAX_ITER:-5}:
2307:452:  Errors fixed: {N}
2308:453:  Errors remaining: {N} (infra: {N}, spec-gap: {N}, pre-existing: {N})
2309:454:  Sonnet agents spawned: {N} (re-verified {M} views)
2310:455:  New errors found: {N}
2311:456:  Matrix coverage: {review_passed}/{total} goals
2312:457:  Map stable: {YES|NO}
2313:458:```
2314:459:
2315:460:### 3e: Iter limit fallback — Diagnostic L2 (RFC v9 D11 + D26, PR-E)
2316:461:
2317:462:When the final iteration (`ITER == MAX_ITER`, default 5) exits with errors STILL
2318:463:remaining (loop hit cap without self-resolving), do NOT silent-BLOCK. Spawn
2319:464:diagnostic_l2 single-advisory fallback:
2320:465:
2321:466:1. Capture residual evidence: list of unresolved error rows from
2322:467:   RUNTIME-MAP + scan-*.json + recipe_executor logs.
2323:468:2. Spawn isolated Haiku subagent (zero parent context — RFC v9 D11) to
2324:469:   classify root cause `block_family` ∈ {schema_drift, validation_bug,
2325:470:   auth_issue, db_constraint, business_logic, integration_failure,
2326:471:   unknown}.
2327:472:3. L2 generates `L2Proposal.json` with confidence + proposed_fix.
2328:473:4. Present to user via single-advisory pattern (D26):
2329:474:     - confidence ≥ 0.7  → "Đề xuất: <fix>. [Yes / chi tiết]"
2330:475:     - confidence < 0.7  → 3-option block_resolve_l3_present (legacy)
2331:476:5. **User gate is mandatory** — never auto-apply (per project policy).
2332:477:6. User accept → apply fix → re-run one extra iteration grace (ITER+1).
2333:478:7. User reject → BLOCK with full audit trail in
2334:479:   `.l2-proposals/{proposal_id}.json` + DEFECT-LOG entry referencing
2335:480:   the proposal.
2336:481:
2337:482:```bash
2338:483:if [ "${ITER:-1}" -eq "${MAX_ITER:-5}" ] && [ -n "${REMAINING_ERRORS}" ] && \
2339:484:   { [ -f "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py" ] || [ -f "${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py" ]; }; then
2340:485:  echo "━━━ Phase 3e — Diagnostic L2 fallback (iter ${ITER} hit cap=${MAX_ITER:-5}) ━━━"
2341:486:  DIAGNOSTIC_L2="${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py"
2342:487:  [ -f "$DIAGNOSTIC_L2" ] || DIAGNOSTIC_L2="${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/spawn-diagnostic-l2.py"
2343:488:  L2_ARGS=(
2344:489:    --phase "${PHASE_NUMBER}"
2345:490:    --gate-id "review.fix_loop"
2346:491:    --evidence-file "${PHASE_DIR}/.fix-loop-evidence.json"
2347:492:  )
2348:493:  L2_OUT=$("${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "$DIAGNOSTIC_L2" \
2349:494:    "${L2_ARGS[@]}" 2>&1)
2350:495:  L2_PROPOSAL_ID=$(echo "$L2_OUT" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "
2351:496:import json, sys
2352:497:try: print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('proposal_id',''))
2353:498:except: print('')
2354:499:")
2355:500:  if [ -n "$L2_PROPOSAL_ID" ]; then
2356:501:    echo "  L2 proposal generated: $L2_PROPOSAL_ID"
2357:502:    # Open DEFECT-LOG entry referencing the proposal
2358:503:    TESTER_PRO_CLI="${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/tester-pro-cli.py"
2359:504:    [ -f "$TESTER_PRO_CLI" ] || TESTER_PRO_CLI="${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/tester-pro-cli.py"
2360:505:    if [ -f "$TESTER_PRO_CLI" ]; then
2361:506:      "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "$TESTER_PRO_CLI" defect new \
2362:507:        --phase "${PHASE_NUMBER}" \
2363:508:        --title "[ITER-LIMIT] Fix loop hit max=${MAX_ITER:-5}, L2 proposal $L2_PROPOSAL_ID" \
2364:509:        --severity major --found-in review \
2365:510:        --notes "L2 proposal at .l2-proposals/${L2_PROPOSAL_ID}.json — user decision pending" \
2366:511:        2>&1 | sed 's/^/  /' || true
2367:512:    fi
2368:513:    # User gate is provider-native after spawn-diagnostic-l2.py:
2369:514:    # Claude Code uses AskUserQuestion; Codex asks in the main thread/UI.
2370:515:    # On accept → run-complete sees applied; on reject → BLOCK below.
2371:516:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
2372:517:      "review.diagnostic_l2_spawned" \
2373:518:      --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"proposal_id\":\"$L2_PROPOSAL_ID\"}" \
2374:519:      >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
2375:520:  fi
2376:521:fi
2377:522:```
2378:523:
2379:524:> **Tại sao không tự apply L2 fix**: L2 đã sai trong dogfood 3.2
2380:525:> (propose fix giả mà có vẻ hợp lý). User gate là single source of truth
2381:526:> cho fix correctness. Audit trail (`.l2-proposals/`) cho phép trace
2382:527:> sau-incident: proposal nào được accept/reject, fix tham chiếu commit nào.
2383:528:</step>
2384:529:
2385:530:<step name="step7_matrix_verdict" mode="full">
2386:531:## Step 7: MATRIX VERDICT (post-fix-loop)
2387:532:
2388:533:→ `narrate_phase "Phase 7 — Goal comparison" "So khớp ${N} goals từ TEST-GOALS với views đã khám phá"`
2389:534:
2390:535:```bash
2391:536:"${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator step-active step7_matrix_verdict >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
2392:537:```
2393:538:
2394:539:### 4.0: RCRURD runtime verification (Task 23 — Codex GPT-5.5 review 2026-05-03)
2395:540:
2396:541:For every TEST-GOALS/G-NN.md with `goal_type: mutation`, run the runtime
2397:542:gate. BLOCK review on assertion fail (R8 update_did_not_apply, etc).
2398:543:Action payload comes from per-phase fixture (`FIXTURES/G-NN.action.json`).
2399:544:
2400:545:```bash
2401:546:EVIDENCE_DIR="${PHASE_DIR}/.rcrurd-evidence"
2402:547:mkdir -p "$EVIDENCE_DIR"
2403:548:RCRURD_FAILED=0
2404:549:RCRURD_RAN=0
2405:550:
2406:551:if [ -d "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS" ]; then
2407:552:  for goal in "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS"/G-*.md; do
2408:553:    [ -f "$goal" ] || continue
2409:554:    grep -qE "goal_type:[[:space:]]*mutation" "$goal" || continue
2410:555:    RCRURD_RAN=$((RCRURD_RAN+1))
2411:556:    ev_out="${EVIDENCE_DIR}/$(basename "$goal" .md).json"
2412:557:
2413:558:    payload="{}"
2414:559:    fixture="${PHASE_DIR}/FIXTURES/$(basename "$goal" .md).action.json"
2415:560:    [ -f "$fixture" ] && payload=$(cat "$fixture")
2416:561:
2417:562:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/validators/verify-rcrurd-runtime.py \
2418:563:      --goal-file "$goal" \
2419:564:      --phase "${PHASE_NUMBER}" \
2420:565:      --action-payload "$payload" \
2421:566:      --auth-header "$(vg_config_get review.rcrurd_auth_header '')" \
2422:567:      --evidence-out "$ev_out" || RCRURD_FAILED=1
2423:568:  done
2424:569:fi
2425:570:
2426:571:if [ "$RCRURD_RAN" -gt 0 ]; then
2427:572:  if [ "$RCRURD_FAILED" = "1" ]; then
2428:573:    echo "⛔ Phase 4.0 RCRURD runtime — at least one mutation goal failed (of ${RCRURD_RAN} run)"
2429:574:    echo "   Evidence: ${EVIDENCE_DIR}/*.json"
2430:575:    echo "   Route through classifier (Task 7) — most are IN_SCOPE for current phase"
2431:576:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
2432:577:      "review.rcrurd_runtime_failed" \
2433:578:      --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"evidence_dir\":\"${EVIDENCE_DIR}\",\"goals_run\":${RCRURD_RAN}}" \
2434:579:      2>/dev/null || true
2435:580:    exit 1
2436:581:  fi
2437:582:
2438:583:  "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" ${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator emit-event \
2439:584:    "review.rcrurd_runtime_passed" \
2440:585:    --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"goals_run\":${RCRURD_RAN}}" \
2441:586:    2>/dev/null || true
2442:587:fi
2443:588:```
2444:589:
2445:590:### 4a: Load Goals + edge cases
2446:591:
2447:592:Load goals via `vg-load --phase ${PHASE_NUMBER} --artifact goals` (generated by /vg:blueprint).
2448:593:If missing → generate from CONTEXT.md + API-CONTRACTS.md (fallback).
2449:594:
2450:595:**P1 v2.49+ — Edge case variants:** also load `${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES/G-NN.md`
2451:596:per goal. Status format extended:
2452:597:- Old: `G-04: PASS` / `G-04: FAIL` / `G-04: NOT_TESTED`
2453:598:- New: `G-04: PASS (5/6 variants — G-04-c1 NOT_TESTED [needs concurrency harness])`
2454:599:
2455:600:For each variant in EDGE-CASES/G-NN.md:
2456:601:- Replay `start_view` (per RUNTIME-MAP) with variant's input
2457:602:- Verify expected_outcome matches actual UI/API response
2458:603:- Mark per-variant: PASS | FAIL | NOT_TESTED (with reason)
2459:604:- Aggregate to goal status (goal PASS only when all critical/high variants PASS)
2460:605:
2461:606:Skip variants when:
2462:607:- EDGE-CASES file missing (legacy phase pre-v2.49) → emit
2463:608:  `review.edge_cases_unavailable` (severity=warn) + treat goal as 1-variant
2464:609:- Variant priority=low + `--skip-low-edge-cases` flag set
2465:610:- No-CRUD phase (CRUD-SURFACES.resources empty) → no variants expected
2466:611:
2467:612:Emit per gate-blocked variant: `review.edge_case_variant_blocked` with
2468:613:`{goal_id, variant_id, reason}` payload.
2469:614:
2470:615:Parse goals: ID, description, success criteria, mutation evidence, dependencies, priority.
2471:616:
2472:617:**Post-build lifecycle contract (v3.6.7) — review MUST consume `/vg:test-spec` artifacts, not only gate their existence.**
2473:618:
2474:619:Load these artifacts before mapping goals:
2475:620:- `${PHASE_DIR}/LIFECYCLE-SPECS.json` — side-effecting / multi-actor lifecycle contract per goal.
2476:621:- `${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-FIXTURE-DAG.json` — fixture dependency graph and cleanup order.
2477:622:- `${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-EXECUTION-PLAN.json` — runner family per phase profile (`web`, `mobile`, `backend`, `cli`, `library`, `mixed`).
2478:623:- `${PHASE_DIR}/DEEP-TEST-SPECS.md` — human-readable provenance and gap context.
2479:624:
2480:625:Review uses them as the lifecycle comparison contract:
2481:626:- Runtime blockers still produce `BLOCKED` and stay in review/debug.
2482:627:- Missing RCRURDR lifecycle proof with clean runtime produces `TEST_PENDING`, then advances to `/vg:test`.
2483:628:- Runner-native phases (`mobile`, `backend`, `cli`, `library`) must not be forced into Playwright/browser semantics; use `TEST-EXECUTION-PLAN.json.family`.
2484:629:- If lifecycle artifacts name a goal that legacy `TEST-GOALS.md` parsing missed, include that goal in `GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md` so review cannot silently drop it.
2485:630:
2486:631:**Surface classification (v1.9.1 R1 — lazy migration, runs BEFORE browser discover decisions):**
2487:632:
2488:633:```bash
2489:634:# shellcheck source=_shared/lib/goal-classifier.sh
2490:635:. ${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/goal-classifier.sh
2491:636:set +e
2492:637:classify_goals_if_needed "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md" "${PHASE_DIR}"
2493:638:gc_rc=$?
2494:639:set -e
2495:640:# rc=2 → provider-native cheap classifier
2496:641:#        Claude: Haiku Task per row; Codex: read-only scanner adapter over pending TSV
2497:642:# rc=3 → provider-native prompt (surface list from config), then classify_goals_apply
2498:643:```
2499:644:
2500:645:Parse `**Surface:** <name>` per goal.
2501:646:
2502:647:**Surface-aware routing (tightened v1.9.1 R1):**
2503:648:
2504:649:For each goal:
2505:650:- `surface == "ui"` / `"ui-mobile"` → proceed with existing browser RUNTIME-MAP lookup below.
2506:651:- `surface ∈ { api, data, time-driven, integration, custom }` → skip browser discover for this goal; instead run lightweight **surface probe**:
2507:652:  * `api`        → grep `apps/**/src/**` for route handler matching contract path → READY if present.
2508:653:  * `data`       → grep migrations + `config.infra_deps` for table/collection → READY if present; INFRA_PENDING if service unavailable.
2509:654:  * `time-driven`→ grep cron/scheduler registration in `apps/workers/**`/`apps/api/**` → READY if handler wired.
2510:655:  * `integration`→ check `${PHASE_DIR}/test-runners/fixtures/${gid}.integration.sh` exists AND downstream caller found → READY.
2511:656:
2512:657:Result feeds GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX with `(status, surface, probe_evidence)`.
2513:658:
2514:659:**Pure-backend fast-path:**
2515:660:```bash
2516:661:UI_GOAL_COUNT=$(grep -c '^\*\*Surface:\*\* ui' "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md" || echo 0)
2517:662:if [ "$UI_GOAL_COUNT" -eq 0 ]; then
2518:663:  echo "🧭 Pure-backend phase (không có goal UI) — bỏ qua browser discovery (khám phá trình duyệt), dùng surface probes." >&2
2519:664:  # Emit empty RUNTIME-MAP if not written yet, skip to 4b
2520:665:  [ -f "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" ] || echo '{"views":{},"goal_sequences":{}}' > "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json"
2521:666:  # Issue #120: runtime_contract still requires one root scan-*.json artifact
2522:667:  # even when backend-only review legitimately skips browser discovery. Emit a
2523:668:  # synthetic backend scan so run-complete does not false-block on must_write.
2524:669:  BACKEND_SCAN_JSON="${PHASE_DIR}/scan-backend-surface-probes.json"
2525:670:  if [ ! -f "$BACKEND_SCAN_JSON" ]; then
2526:671:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" - "$BACKEND_SCAN_JSON" <<'PY'
2527:672:import json
2528:673:import sys
2529:674:from datetime import datetime, timezone
2530:675:from pathlib import Path
2531:676:
2532:677:payload = {
2533:678:    "view": "backend://surface-probes",
2534:679:    "surface": "backend",
2535:680:    "generated_by": "step7_matrix_verdict.pure_backend_fastpath",
2536:681:    "generated_at": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat().replace("+00:00", "Z"),
2537:682:    "results": [],
2538:683:    "forms": [],
2539:684:    "tables": [],
2540:685:    "modal_triggers": [],
2541:686:    "sub_views_discovered": [],
2542:687:}
2543:688:Path(sys.argv[1]).write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2) + "\n", encoding="utf-8")
2544:689:PY
2545:690:  fi
2546:691:fi
2547:692:```
2548:693:
2549:694:**Mixed-phase surface probe execution (v1.9.2.3 P3):**
2550:695:
2551:696:For phases có CẢ UI goals (cần browser) VÀ backend goals (api/data/integration/time-driven), browser phase chỉ cover UI goals. Backend goals PHẢI được probe SEPARATELY để avoid rơi vào NOT_SCANNED branch.
2552:697:
2553:698:```bash
2554:699:# Run surface probes cho goals có surface ≠ ui
2555:700:source "${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/surface-probe.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
2556:701:if type -t run_surface_probe >/dev/null 2>&1; then
2557:702:  PROBE_RESULTS_JSON="${PHASE_DIR}/.surface-probe-results.json"
2558:703:  echo '{"probed_at":"'"$(date -u +%FT%TZ)"'","results":{' > "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
2559:704:  FIRST=true
2560:705:
2561:706:  # Extract goal_id + surface pairs from TEST-GOALS.md
2562:707:  ${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
2563:708:import re
2564:709:tg = open('${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md', encoding='utf-8').read()
2565:710:for gid, surface in re.findall(r'^## Goal (G-[\w]+):.*?^\*\*Surface:\*\* (\w[\w-]*)', tg, re.M|re.S):
2566:711:    print(f'{gid} {surface}')
2567:712:" | while read -r gid surface; do
2568:713:    surface="${surface%$'\r'}"
2569:714:    # Skip UI — browser phase handles them
2570:715:    [ "$surface" = "ui" ] || [ "$surface" = "ui-mobile" ] && continue
2571:716:
2572:717:    PROBE=$(run_surface_probe "$gid" "$surface" "$PHASE_DIR" 2>/dev/null)
2573:718:    STATUS=$(echo "$PROBE" | cut -d'|' -f1)
2574:719:    EVIDENCE=$(echo "$PROBE" | cut -d'|' -f2- | sed 's/"/\\"/g')
2575:720:
2576:721:    [ "$FIRST" = "true" ] && FIRST=false || echo "," >> "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
2577:722:    printf '"%s":{"surface":"%s","status":"%s","evidence":"%s"}' \
2578:723:           "$gid" "$surface" "$STATUS" "$EVIDENCE" >> "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
2579:724:  done
2580:725:
2581:726:  echo '}}' >> "$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON"
2582:727:
2583:728:  # Summary narration
2584:729:  PROBED=$(${PYTHON_BIN} -c "
2585:730:import json
2586:731:d = json.load(open('$PROBE_RESULTS_JSON'))['results']
2587:732:from collections import Counter
2588:733:c = Counter(r['status'] for r in d.values())
2589:734:print(f'Phase 4a surface probes: {len(d)} backend goals probed → {dict(c)}')")
2590:735:  echo "▸ $PROBED"
2591:736:
2592:737:  # v2.48.1 (Issue #85) — backfill synthetic goal_sequences[gid] for non-UI
2593:738:  # goals from probe results so verify-matrix-evidence-link.py (which only
2594:739:  # inspects RUNTIME-MAP goal_sequences[]) sees backend evidence. Closes the
2595:740:  # surface-probe schema gap that BLOCKed Phase 3.2 dogfood with 32 non-UI
2596:741:  # READY goals flagged matrix_status_without_runtime_sequence.
2597:742:  # Idempotent: re-runs overwrite synthetic entries by gid, never overwrites
2598:743:  # real browser-recorded sequences.
2599:744:  if [ -f "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/backfill-surface-probe-runtime.py" ]; then
2600:745:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/backfill-surface-probe-runtime.py" \
2601:746:      --phase-dir "$PHASE_DIR" 2>&1 | sed 's/^/▸ /' || true
2602:747:  fi
2603:748:fi
2604:749:```
2605:750:
2606:751:**Phase 4b integration:** Khi check goal_sequences cho backend goals (surface ≠ ui), trước khi mark NOT_SCANNED hãy check `.surface-probe-results.json`:
2607:752:- Nếu probe READY → map → STATUS: READY với evidence từ probe (handler path, migration file, caller reference).
2608:753:- Nếu probe BLOCKED → map → STATUS: BLOCKED với evidence là probe reason.
2609:754:- Nếu probe INFRA_PENDING → map → STATUS: INFRA_PENDING.
2610:755:- Nếu probe SKIPPED (can't parse criteria) → fallthrough to NOT_SCANNED branch → buộc user cải thiện TEST-GOALS hoặc override.
2611:756:
2612:757:**Lifecycle contract integration (v3.6.7):**
2613:758:- If `LIFECYCLE-SPECS.json.goals[G-XX]` exists and runtime/probe found a real API/render/data blocker → keep `BLOCKED`.
2614:759:- If runtime/probe is clean but RCRURDR stages, fixture DAG, actor handoff, artifact capture, or cleanup are not proven by review evidence → mark `TEST_PENDING`, not `BLOCKED`.
2615:760:- If no browser sequence exists for a runner-native lifecycle goal (`family in {mobile, backend, cli, library}`) → mark `TEST_PENDING` with runner/family evidence from `TEST-EXECUTION-PLAN.json`.
2616:761:- If a web lifecycle goal has no `goal_sequences[G-XX]` → keep `NOT_SCANNED`; review must still discover the route/action before `/vg:test` can generate reliable replay steps.
2617:762:
2618:763:**Infra dependency filter (config-driven):**
2619:764:
2620:765:If goal has `**Infra deps:**` field (e.g., `[clickhouse, kafka, pixel_server]`):
2621:766:```bash
2622:767:# Check each infra dep against current environment
2623:768:for dep in goal.infra_deps:
2624:769:  SERVICE_CHECK=$(read config.infra_deps.services[dep].check_${ENV})
2625:770:  if ! eval "$SERVICE_CHECK" 2>/dev/null; then
2626:771:    goal.status = "INFRA_PENDING"
2627:772:    goal.skip_reason = "${dep} not available on ${ENV}"
2628:773:  fi
2629:774:done
2630:775:```
2631:776:
2632:777:Goals classified as `INFRA_PENDING` are **excluded from gate calculation** (when `config.infra_deps.unmet_behavior == "skip"`). They don't count as BLOCKED or FAIL — they're simply not testable on current environment.
2633:778:
2634:779:Display: `INFRA_PENDING ({dep})` in matrix with distinct icon.
2635:780:
2636:781:**Console noise filter (config-driven):**
2637:782:
2638:783:When evaluating console errors from Phase 2 discovery, filter against `config.console_noise.patterns`:
2639:784:```bash
2640:785:if [ "${config_console_noise_enabled}" = "true" ]; then
2641:786:  for pattern in config.console_noise.patterns:
2642:787:    # Remove matching errors from bug list — classify as INFRA_NOISE
2643:788:    REAL_ERRORS=$(echo "$ALL_CONSOLE_ERRORS" | grep -viE "$pattern")
2644:789:  done
2645:790:  NOISE_COUNT=$((TOTAL_ERRORS - REAL_ERROR_COUNT))
2646:791:  echo "Console: ${REAL_ERROR_COUNT} real errors, ${NOISE_COUNT} infra noise (filtered)"
2647:792:fi
2648:793:```
2649:794:
2650:795:Only REAL_ERRORS (not matching noise patterns) count as view failures.
2651:796:
2652:797:### 4b: Map Goals to RUNTIME-MAP
2653:798:
2654:799:For each goal, check goal_sequences in RUNTIME-MAP.json:
2655:800:
2656:801:```
2657:802:For each goal:
2658:803:  IF goal_sequences[goal_id] exists AND result == "passed":
2659:804:    → STATUS: READY (goal was verified during Pass 2a)
2660:805:
2661:806:  IF goal_sequences[goal_id] exists AND result == "failed":
2662:807:    → STATUS: BLOCKED (with specific failure steps from goal_sequence)
2663:808:
2664:809:  IF goal_sequences[goal_id] does NOT exist:
2665:810:    # Before marking UNREACHABLE, verify code presence to distinguish
2666:811:    # true "not built" from "built but not scanned"
2667:812:    code_exists = check via grep against config.code_patterns:
2668:813:      - Does goal's expected page file exist? (e.g., FloorRulesListPage.tsx)
2669:814:      - Is the route registered? (e.g., /floor-rules in router)
2670:815:      - Do related API endpoints have handlers? (grep API-CONTRACTS vs apps/api/)
2671:816:
2672:817:    IF code_exists == FALSE:
2673:818:      → STATUS: UNREACHABLE (feature not built — fix with /vg:build --gaps-only)
2674:819:
2675:820:    IF code_exists == TRUE:
2676:821:      → STATUS: NOT_SCANNED (intermediate only — MUST resolve before review exits)
2677:822:      Root cause likely one of:
2678:823:        - Multi-step wizard/mutation needs dedicated browser session
2679:824:        - Goal path not reachable from discovered sidebar (orphan route)
2680:825:        - Review ran --retry-failed but this goal wasn't in retry set
2681:826:        - Haiku agent timed out or skipped
2682:827:        - Goal has no UI surface but TEST-GOALS didn't mark infra_deps
2683:828:      → RESOLUTION (tightened 2026-04-17 — NOT_SCANNED không được defer sang /vg:test):
2684:829:        NOT_SCANNED là trạng thái TRUNG GIAN, KHÔNG phải kết luận hợp lệ.
2685:830:        Review PHẢI resolve thành 1 trong 4 status kết luận: READY | BLOCKED | UNREACHABLE | INFRA_PENDING
2686:831:        Cách resolve (pick 1):
2687:832:          a) /vg:review {phase} --retry-failed với deeper probe (nếu timeout/depth issue)
2688:833:          b) Goal không có UI surface → update TEST-GOALS với `**Infra deps:** [<user-defined no-ui tag>]` → re-classify INFRA_PENDING (tag value do user định nghĩa trong config.infra_deps, workflow không hardcode)
2689:834:          c) Orphan/hidden route → verify config.code_patterns.frontend_routes đã cover pattern đó
2690:835:          d) Genuinely unreachable (feature đã build nhưng UX path không exist) → manually mark UNREACHABLE with reason note
2691:836:```
2692:837:
2693:838:**Status semantics (tightened 2026-04-17):**
2694:839:
2695:840:4 **status kết luận hợp lệ** (chỉ 4 status này được write vào GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX final):
2696:841:
2697:842:| Status | Meaning | Fix command |
2698:843:|---|---|---|
2699:844:| READY | Goal verified, evidence in goal_sequences | none |
2700:845:| BLOCKED | View found, scan ran, criteria failed | fix code → `--retry-failed` |
2701:846:| UNREACHABLE | Code not in repo / UX path không exist | `/vg:build --gaps-only` |
2702:847:| INFRA_PENDING | Goal needs service/infra not available on ENV | deploy infra or sandbox |
2703:848:
2704:849:2 **status trung gian** (PHẢI resolve trước khi exit Phase 4):
2705:850:
2706:851:| Status | Meaning | Action BẮT BUỘC |
2707:852:|---|---|---|
2708:853:| NOT_SCANNED | Code exists, review didn't replay | `--retry-failed` HOẶC re-classify thành 1 trong 4 status trên |
2709:854:| FAILED | Scan timeout/exception | check logs → `--retry-failed` |
2710:855:
2711:856:**⛔ GLOBAL RULE: KHÔNG được defer NOT_SCANNED sang /vg:test.**
2712:857:
2713:858:Lý do: `/vg:test` codegen LẤY steps từ `goal_sequences[]` mà review ghi. NOT_SCANNED = review không ghi sequence = codegen không có input. Test không phải fallback cho review miss.
2714:859:
2715:860:Goals không có UI surface đúng ra phải mark `infra_deps: [<no-ui tag>]` trong TEST-GOALS (tag value do project config quy ước) → skip ở review (INFRA_PENDING) → test qua integration/unit layer ở build phase, KHÔNG qua /vg:test E2E.
2716:861:
2717:862:### 4c-pre: ⛔ NOT_SCANNED resolution gate (tightened 2026-04-17)
2718:863:
2719:864:Trước khi chạy weighted gate, PHẢI resolve mọi `NOT_SCANNED` + `FAILED` thành 1 trong 4 kết luận.
2720:865:
2721:866:```bash
2722:867:# OHOK-8 round-4 Codex fix: replace pseudocode with real bash grep.
2723:868:# Previously `count goals where status == "NOT_SCANNED"` was not executable
2724:869:# → gate couldn't run → NOT_SCANNED goals slipped through unresolved.
2725:870:MATRIX="${PHASE_DIR}/GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md"
2726:871:NOT_SCANNED_COUNT=$(grep -cE '^\| G-[0-9]+.*\|[[:space:]]*NOT_SCANNED[[:space:]]*\|' "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)
2727:872:FAILED_COUNT=$(grep -cE '^\| G-[0-9]+.*\|[[:space:]]*FAILED[[:space:]]*\|' "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)
2728:873:INTERMEDIATE=$((NOT_SCANNED_COUNT + FAILED_COUNT))
2729:874:# Build the list of intermediate goal IDs (used later in override auto-convert)
2730:875:INTERMEDIATE_GOALS=$(grep -oE '^\| (G-[0-9]+)[^|]*\|[^|]*\|[^|]*\|[[:space:]]*(NOT_SCANNED|FAILED)[[:space:]]*\|' "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null \
2731:876:  | grep -oE 'G-[0-9]+' | sort -u | tr '\n' ' ')
2732:877:
2733:878:if [ "$INTERMEDIATE" -gt 0 ]; then
2734:879:  echo "⛔ Review cannot exit Phase 4 — ${INTERMEDIATE} intermediate goals:"
2735:880:  echo "   NOT_SCANNED: ${NOT_SCANNED_COUNT}"
2736:881:  echo "   FAILED:      ${FAILED_COUNT}"
2737:882:  echo ""
2738:883:  echo "Intermediate ≠ conclusion. Resolve before exit:"
2739:884:  echo "  a) /vg:review ${PHASE_NUMBER} --retry-failed  (deeper probe)"
2740:885:  echo "  b) Update TEST-GOALS with 'Infra deps: [backend_only]' nếu goal không có UI"
2741:886:  echo "     → re-classify INFRA_PENDING"
2742:887:  echo "  c) Fix config.code_patterns.frontend_routes nếu route ẩn khỏi sidebar"
2743:888:  echo "  d) Manual re-classify UNREACHABLE (feature không tồn tại) với reason note"
2744:889:  echo ""
2745:890:  echo "⛔ KHÔNG ĐƯỢC defer sang /vg:test để 'cover' NOT_SCANNED goals."
2746:891:  echo "   Test codegen lấy input từ goal_sequences review ghi. NOT_SCANNED = no input."
2747:892:  echo ""
2748:893:  echo "Override (NOT RECOMMENDED — creates debt):"
2749:894:  echo "  /vg:review ${PHASE_NUMBER} --allow-intermediate"
2750:895:  echo "  → Auto-convert remaining NOT_SCANNED → UNREACHABLE với reason='review-skip'"
2751:896:  echo "  → Logged to GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md 'Debt' section"
2752:897:
2753:898:  if [[ ! "$ARGUMENTS" =~ --allow-intermediate ]]; then
2754:899:    # v1.9.1 R2+R4: block-resolver — try L1 auto-fix (re-scan failed goals) before demanding user override.
2755:900:    # If L1 fails, L2 architect proposal is presented through provider-native L3 prompt.
2756:901:    # L4 only when L2 proposal rejected AND no user direction.
2757:902:    # See _shared/lib/block-resolver.sh
2758:903:    source "${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/block-resolver.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
2759:904:    if type -t block_resolve >/dev/null 2>&1; then
2760:905:      export VG_CURRENT_PHASE="$PHASE_NUMBER" VG_CURRENT_STEP="review.4c-pre"
2761:906:      BR_GATE_CONTEXT="NOT_SCANNED/FAILED goals block review exit. ${INTERMEDIATE} intermediate goals need conclusion (READY/BLOCKED/UNREACHABLE/INFRA_PENDING)."
2762:907:      BR_EVIDENCE=$(printf '{"not_scanned":%d,"failed":%d,"total_intermediate":%d}' "$NOT_SCANNED_COUNT" "$FAILED_COUNT" "$INTERMEDIATE")
2763:908:      BR_CANDIDATES='[{"id":"retry-failed-scan","cmd":"echo retry-failed auto-fix would re-trigger scanner for FAILED goals only; skipping in safe mode","confidence":0.5,"rationale":"retry-failed probe may reclassify goals without human override"}]'
2764:909:      BR_RESULT=$(block_resolve "not-scanned-defer" "$BR_GATE_CONTEXT" "$BR_EVIDENCE" "$PHASE_DIR" "$BR_CANDIDATES")
2765:910:      BR_LEVEL=$(echo "$BR_RESULT" | ${PYTHON_BIN} -c "import json,sys; print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('level',''))" 2>/dev/null)
2766:911:      if [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L1" ]; then
2767:912:        echo "✓ Block resolver L1 self-resolved — intermediate goals auto-fixed"
2768:913:      elif [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L2" ]; then
2769:914:        block_resolve_l2_handoff "not-scanned-defer" "$BR_RESULT" "$PHASE_DIR"
2770:915:        echo "  Để proceed sau khi user chấp nhận proposal: re-run /vg:review ${PHASE_NUMBER} --allow-intermediate --reason='<applied proposal>'" >&2
2771:916:        exit 2
2772:917:      else
2773:918:        # L4 truly stuck — print human-direction message
2774:919:        block_resolve_l4_stuck "not-scanned-defer" "L1 failed + L2 produced no actionable proposal"
2775:920:        exit 1
2776:921:      fi
2777:922:    else
2778:923:      exit 1
2779:924:    fi
2780:925:  else
2781:926:    # v1.9.0 T1: rationalization guard — NOT_SCANNED defer is a classic rationalization surface.
2782:927:    RATGUARD_RESULT=$(rationalization_guard_check "not-scanned-defer" \
2783:928:      "NOT_SCANNED = review didn't replay the goal sequence. Deferring = test codegen has no input. Auto-UNREACHABLE hides coverage debt." \
2784:929:      "intermediate_goals=${INTERMEDIATE_GOALS} not_scanned=${NOT_SCANNED_COUNT} failed=${FAILED_COUNT}")
2785:930:    if ! rationalization_guard_dispatch "$RATGUARD_RESULT" "not-scanned-defer" "--allow-intermediate" "$PHASE_NUMBER" "review.4c-pre" "${INTERMEDIATE} intermediate goals"; then
2786:931:      exit 1
2787:932:    fi
2788:933:    # OHOK-8 round-4 Codex fix: update_goal_status was undefined function.
2789:934:    # Replaced with real bash sed that rewrites matrix row in-place.
2790:935:    # Auto-convert intermediate → UNREACHABLE với audit trail.
2791:936:    TS=$(date -u +%FT%TZ)
2792:937:    for gid in $INTERMEDIATE_GOALS; do
2793:938:      # Match row `| G-XX |...|...|...| (NOT_SCANNED|FAILED) |`, replace
2794:939:      # status column only. Preserve other columns. Use | delimiter in sed
2795:940:      # to avoid conflicts with pipe chars in evidence.
2796:941:      sed -i -E "s|^(\| ${gid} \|[^|]+\|[^|]+\|[^|]+\|)[[:space:]]*(NOT_SCANNED\|FAILED)[[:space:]]*\|(.*)$|\1 UNREACHABLE |review-skip-\2 @${TS}\3|" \
2797:942:        "$MATRIX" 2>/dev/null || true
2798:943:    done
2799:944:    echo "intermediate-override: ${INTERMEDIATE} goals auto-converted UNREACHABLE ts=$(date -u +%FT%TZ)" \
2800:945:      >> "${PHASE_DIR}/build-state.log"
2801:946:  fi
2802:947:fi
2803:948:```
2804:949:
2805:950:### 4c: Write GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md (v1.9.2.4 runnable merger)
2806:951:
2807:952:```bash
2808:953:# Call matrix-merger.sh helper — reads RUNTIME-MAP + probe-results + TEST-GOALS,
2809:954:# computes per-goal status with priority precedence (browser > probe > code_exists),
2810:955:# writes canonical GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md with summary + by-priority + details + gate.
2811:956:source "${VG_COMMAND_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/commands/vg}/_shared/lib/matrix-merger.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
2812:957:if type -t merge_and_write_matrix >/dev/null 2>&1; then
2813:958:  MERGE_OUTPUT=$(merge_and_write_matrix "$PHASE_DIR" \
2814:959:    "${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS.md" \
2815:960:    "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" \
2816:961:    "${PHASE_DIR}/.surface-probe-results.json" \
2817:962:    "${PHASE_DIR}/GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md" 2>&1)
2818:963:
2819:964:  # Extract machine-readable counts + verdict
2820:965:  VERDICT=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^VERDICT=' | cut -d= -f2)
2821:966:  READY=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^READY=' | cut -d= -f2)
2822:967:  BLOCKED=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^BLOCKED=' | cut -d= -f2)
2823:968:  TEST_PENDING=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^TEST_PENDING=' | cut -d= -f2)
2824:969:  NOT_SCANNED=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^NOT_SCANNED=' | cut -d= -f2)
2825:970:  INTERMEDIATE=$(echo "$MERGE_OUTPUT" | grep '^INTERMEDIATE=' | cut -d= -f2)
2826:971:  export VERDICT READY BLOCKED TEST_PENDING NOT_SCANNED INTERMEDIATE
2827:972:
2828:973:  echo "✓ GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md: VERDICT=$VERDICT (ready=$READY blocked=$BLOCKED test_pending=$TEST_PENDING not_scanned=$NOT_SCANNED)"
2829:974:else
2830:975:  echo "⚠ matrix-merger.sh missing — falling back to manual matrix write (legacy path)"
2831:976:  # Legacy path: orchestrator writes matrix directly using template below
2832:977:fi
2833:978:
2834:979:# Bind GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md + RUNTIME-MAP.json provenance to both runtime
2835:980:# evidence and post-build lifecycle artifacts. This makes run-complete catch
2836:981:# stale matrix reuse, lifecycle-spec drift, AND stale runtime-map reuse after
2837:982:# review. Closes #175: must_write artifacts existed on disk but had no
2838:983:# evidence-manifest entries → manual emit-evidence-manifest calls required.
2839:984:EMIT_MANIFEST="${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/emit-evidence-manifest.py"
2840:985:[ -f "$EMIT_MANIFEST" ] || EMIT_MANIFEST="${REPO_ROOT}/scripts/emit-evidence-manifest.py"
2841:986:if [ -f "$EMIT_MANIFEST" ]; then
2842:987:  if [ -f "${PHASE_DIR}/RUNTIME-MAP.json" ]; then
2843:988:    set +e
2844:989:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "$EMIT_MANIFEST" \
