3490:81:@${PHASE_DIR}/FIXTURES-CACHE.json        (if exists — fixture inject)
3491:82:@${PHASE_DIR}/CRUD-SURFACES.md           (if exists — CRUD structural fallback)
3492:83:@${PHASE_DIR}/LIFECYCLE-SPECS.json       (fixture DAG + actors + RCRURDR stages for mutation/multi-actor goals)
3493:84:@${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS-DISCOVERED.md   (if exists — G-AUTO-* skeleton specs)
3494:85:@${PHASE_DIR}/TEST-GOALS-EXPANDED.md     (if exists — G-CRUD-* skeleton specs)
3495:86:@${PHASE_DIR}/SEED-RECIPE.md             (Batch 51+52 — per-variant seed/cleanup contract)
3496:87:@${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES/                (Batch 48 — per-goal variant_id list)
3497:88:@${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES/VARIANTS.json   (Batch 56 — machine-readable variants index; PREFER this over markdown parsing)
3498:89:</inputs>
3499:90:
3500:91:<seed_contract>
3501:92:Batch 52: every `test.each([variant])` row generated from EDGE-CASES /
3502:93:LIFECYCLE-SPECS edge_cases[] / negative_specs[] MUST be wrapped with seed
3503:94:binding from SEED-RECIPE.md. Without seed wrap, tests run on undefined
3504:95:state → drift (Batch 51 documented the cascade).
3505:96:
3506:97:For each variant_id in spec:
3507:98:  1. Parse SEED-RECIPE.md ```yaml fences. Match variant_id field.
3508:99:  2. Emit `beforeEach(async () => { await runSeedRecipe('${variant_id}'); })`
3509:100:     OR inline seed_action from recipe (per project convention).
3510:101:  3. Emit `afterEach(async () => { await cleanup('${variant_id}'); })`
3511:102:     OR inline cleanup from recipe.
3512:103:  4. If recipe has `idempotent: false`, add note in test comment:
3513:104:     `// Seed not idempotent — test order matters`.
3514:105:
3515:106:Sample emission per variant:
3516:107:```ts
3517:108:test.each(variants)('${variant_id} — ${label}', async ({ page }, variant) => {
3518:109:  // vg-edge-case: ${variant_id}
3519:110:  // seed recipe: ${SEED-RECIPE.md#${variant_id}}
3520:111:  // requires_state: ${requires_state}
3521:112:  await runSeedRecipe(variant.id);
3522:113:  try {
3523:114:    // ... test body using variant.input_hint
3524:115:    // ... expect() per variant.expected
3525:116:  } finally {
3526:117:    await cleanup(variant.id);
3527:118:  }
3528:119:});
3529:120:```
3530:121:
3531:122:If SEED-RECIPE entry has `<PLACEHOLDER>` values, emit `// TODO seed:
3532:123:fill seed_action / cleanup per project schema before running` instead
3533:124:of inline action. Spec body still binds variant_id reference.
3534:125:
3535:126:**Batch 56 — source-of-truth for `variants` array.** When
3536:127:${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES/VARIANTS.json exists (Batch 56), prefer it
3537:128:over markdown parsing. Each goal_id entry has a list of variant rows
3538:129:with strict fields (variant_id, kind, label, input_hint, expected,
3539:130:source, priority, idempotent). Generated spec imports the goal's
3540:131:variants as a JSON literal:
