3815:406:## Step F — L1/L2 binding gate
3816:407:
3817:408:### F.1 — R7 console monitoring enforcement gate
3818:409:
3819:410:Verify generated mutation specs have console assertion:
3820:411:
3821:412:```python
3822:413:import json, re, sys, os
3823:414:from pathlib import Path
3824:415:
3825:416:# Batch 47 H: prefer CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json as canonical spec list over glob.
3826:417:# Manifest has authoritative goal_id binding; glob may pick up stale orphans.
3827:418:tests_dir = Path("${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}")
3828:419:manifest_path = Path("${PHASE_DIR}/CODEGEN-MANIFEST.json")
3829:420:spec_files = []
3830:421:if manifest_path.is_file():
3831:422:    try:
3832:423:        m = json.loads(manifest_path.read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
3833:424:        entries = m.get("playwright_specs") or m.get("specs") or []
3834:425:        for e in entries:
3835:426:            p = e.get("path") if isinstance(e, dict) else str(e)
3836:427:            if not p:
3837:428:                continue
3838:429:            cand = Path(p) if Path(p).is_absolute() else Path.cwd() / p
3839:430:            if cand.is_file():
3840:431:                spec_files.append(cand)
3841:432:    except Exception:
3842:433:        spec_files = []
3843:434:if not spec_files:
3844:435:    # Fallback: glob (legacy phase or manifest absent)
3845:436:    spec_files = list(tests_dir.rglob("*.spec.ts"))
3846:437:
3847:438:SETUP_PATTERNS = [
3848:439:    r'window\.__consoleErrors',
3849:440:    r'page\.on\s*\(\s*[\'"]console[\'"]',
3850:441:    r'captureConsoleErrors',
3851:442:]
3852:443:ASSERT_PATTERNS = [
3853:444:    r'expect\s*\(\s*(?:errs|consoleErrors|window\.__consoleErrors)[\[\.\w]*\s*\)\.toBe\s*\(\s*0\s*\)',
3854:445:    r'expect\s*\(\s*.*console.*\)\.toBe(?:Less|Equal)',
3855:446:]
3856:447:MUTATION_PATTERNS = [
3857:448:    r'(?:POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE)\s+',
3858:449:    r'waitForResponse.*(?:post|put|patch|delete)',
3859:450:]
3860:451:
3861:452:violations = []
3862:453:for spec in spec_files:
3863:454:    content = spec.read_text(encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore')
3864:455:    has_mutation = any(re.search(p, content, re.IGNORECASE) for p in MUTATION_PATTERNS)
3865:456:    has_assert = any(re.search(p, content) for p in ASSERT_PATTERNS)
3866:457:    if has_mutation and not has_assert:
3867:458:        violations.append(spec.name)
3868:459:
3869:460:if violations:
3870:461:    # BLOCK — emit in l2_escalations if block-resolver fails
3871:462:    pass
3872:463:```
3873:464:
3874:465:Override: `--allow-missing-console-check` (logs override-debt).
