3887:478:### F.2.5 — edge-case variant coverage gate (P1 v2.49+)
3888:479:
3889:480:Before goal-test binding gate, verify each variant from EDGE-CASES has a
3890:481:matching `test()` or `test.each()` row in generated `.spec.ts`:
3891:482:
3892:483:```bash
3893:484:# Batch 45 F6 fix: deterministic gate — no env-var dependency.
3894:485:# Previously relied on EDGE_CASES_AVAILABLE / GOALS_LIST / ALLOW_SKIP
3895:486:# which no orchestrator step set → gate was dead code.
3896:487:if [ -d "${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES" ]; then
3897:488:  EDGE_GAP_COUNT=0
3898:489:  # Iterate EDGE-CASES/G-*.md directly — derive goal list inline.
3899:490:  for EDGE_FILE in "${PHASE_DIR}/EDGE-CASES/"G-*.md; do
3900:491:    [ -f "$EDGE_FILE" ] || continue
3901:492:    gid=$(basename "$EDGE_FILE" .md)
3902:493:
3903:494:    # Extract variant_ids from edge case file (G-NN-a1, G-NN-b2, etc.)
3904:495:    VARIANTS=$(grep -oE "${gid}-[a-z][0-9]+" "$EDGE_FILE" | sort -u)
3905:496:    for vid in $VARIANTS; do
3906:497:      # Variant must appear in spec.ts comment OR test name
3907:498:      if ! grep -rqE "vg-edge-case[: ]+${vid}|test\\(['\"].*${vid}|test\\.each.*${vid}" "${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}/" 2>/dev/null; then
3908:499:        echo "  ⚠ ${gid}: variant ${vid} không có test (spec.ts thiếu coverage)"
3909:500:        EDGE_GAP_COUNT=$((EDGE_GAP_COUNT + 1))
3910:501:      fi
3911:502:    done
3912:503:  done
3913:504:  if [ "$EDGE_GAP_COUNT" -gt 0 ]; then
3914:505:    echo "⛔ Batch 45 F6: ${EDGE_GAP_COUNT} variant(s) không có test coverage."
3915:506:    echo "   AI phải re-codegen với test.each(...) per variant từ EDGE-CASES."
3916:507:    echo "   Reference variant_id ở comment hoặc test name."
3917:508:    "${PYTHON_BIN:-python3}" "${VG_SCRIPT_ROOT:-${VG_HOME:-$HOME/.vgflow}/scripts}/vg-orchestrator" \
3918:509:      emit-event "test.edge_coverage_failed" \
3919:510:      --payload "{\"phase\":\"${PHASE_NUMBER}\",\"gaps\":${EDGE_GAP_COUNT}}" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
3920:511:    if [[ ! "${ARGUMENTS:-}" =~ --skip-edge-coverage ]]; then
3921:512:      exit 1
3922:513:    fi
3923:514:    echo "⚠ --skip-edge-coverage set — proceeding with ${EDGE_GAP_COUNT} gap(s) (debt logged)"
3924:515:  fi
3925:516:fi
3926:517:```
3927:518:
3928:519:Severity: BLOCK by default; degrades to WARN if `--allow-edge-case-gap` flag
3929:520:set (paired with override-reason).
3930:521:
3931:522:### F.3 — goal-test binding gate (verify-goal-test-binding.py)
3932:523:
3933:524:After R7 gate and adversarial gate, run the binding verification:
3934:525:
3935:526:```bash
3936:527:GTB_MODE=$(vg_config_get build_gates.goal_test_binding_phase_end strict)
3937:528:if [ "$GTB_MODE" != "off" ]; then
3938:529:  PHASE_FIRST_COMMIT=$(git log --format="%H" --reverse --grep="${PHASE_NUMBER}-" | head -1)
3939:530:  SCAN_TAG="${PHASE_FIRST_COMMIT:+${PHASE_FIRST_COMMIT}^}"
3940:531:  SCAN_TAG="${SCAN_TAG:-HEAD~200}"
3941:532:
3942:533:  GTB_ARGS="--phase-dir ${PHASE_DIR} --wave-tag ${SCAN_TAG} --wave-number phase-end"
3943:534:  [ "$GTB_MODE" = "warn" ] && GTB_ARGS="${GTB_ARGS} --lenient"
3944:535:
3945:536:  if ! ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} .claude/scripts/verify-goal-test-binding.py ${GTB_ARGS}; then
3946:537:    echo "⛔ Goal-test binding FAILED."
3947:538:
3948:539:    # Attempt L1 via block-resolver (re-codegen candidate)
3949:540:    source "${REPO_ROOT}/.claude/commands/vg/_shared/lib/block-resolver.sh" 2>/dev/null || true
3950:541:    if type -t block_resolve >/dev/null 2>&1; then
3951:542:      export VG_CURRENT_PHASE="${PHASE_NUMBER}" VG_CURRENT_STEP="test.5b-goal-test-binding"
3952:543:      BR_GATE_CTX="Goal-test binding gate: plan tasks claim goals but no corresponding test file found."
3953:544:      BR_EVIDENCE=$(printf '{"gate":"goal_test_binding_phase_end","generated_tests_dir":"%s","mode":"%s"}' "$GENERATED_TESTS_DIR" "$GTB_MODE")
3954:545:      BR_CANDIDATES='[{"id":"recodegen","cmd":"echo L1-SAFE: would invoke codegen-only rerun; exit 1","confidence":0.6,"rationale":"codegen drift is most common cause"}]'
3955:546:      BR_RESULT=$(block_resolve "goal-test-binding" "$BR_GATE_CTX" "$BR_EVIDENCE" "$PHASE_DIR" "$BR_CANDIDATES")
3956:547:      BR_LEVEL=$(echo "$BR_RESULT" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "import json,sys; print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('level',''))" 2>/dev/null)
3957:548:      if [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L1" ]; then
3958:549:        echo "✓ L1 resolved — re-run verification"
3959:550:        ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} .claude/scripts/verify-goal-test-binding.py ${GTB_ARGS}
3960:551:        L1_RESOLVED=$((L1_RESOLVED + 1))
3961:552:      elif [ "$BR_LEVEL" = "L2" ]; then
3962:553:        # L2: package architect proposal for return JSON l2_escalations
3963:554:        block_resolve_l2_handoff "goal-test-binding" "$BR_RESULT" "$PHASE_DIR"
3964:555:        L2_ITEMS+=("goal-test-binding|$(echo "$BR_RESULT" | ${PYTHON_BIN:-python3} -c "import json,sys; print(json.loads(sys.stdin.read()).get('architect_proposal',''))" 2>/dev/null)|binding gate failed")
3965:556:      else
3966:557:        block_resolve_l4_stuck "goal-test-binding" "L1 re-codegen failed, L2 architect unavailable"
3967:558:        BINDING_FAILED=true
3968:559:      fi
3969:560:    else
3970:561:      BINDING_FAILED=true
3971:562:    fi
3972:563:  fi
3973:564:fi
3974:565:```
3975:566:
3976:567:**L1/L2 binding gate summary:**
3977:568:
3978:569:| Outcome | Behavior |
3979:570:|---|---|
3980:571:| Binding passes | Continue to return JSON. |
3981:572:| L1 self-resolved | `l1_resolved_count` incremented; re-verify passes. |
3982:573:| L2 needed | Package `architect_proposal` text into `l2_escalations`; main agent handles via `AskUserQuestion`. |
3983:574:| L4 stuck | Binding FAILED recorded; main agent sees `binding_failed: true`. |
3984:575:
3985:576:The `5d_binding_gate` step is NOT marked at orchestrator level — it is
3986:577:subagent-internal. The binding gate's `verify-goal-test-binding.py` call
3987:578:and the block-resolver L1/L2 loop are both fully contained here.
3988:579:
3989:580:## Return JSON envelope
3990:581:
3991:582:After all steps complete, return:
3992:583:
3993:584:```json
3994:585:{
3995:586:  "spec_files": [
3996:587:    "${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}/${PHASE_NUMBER}-goal-G-01.spec.ts",
3997:588:    "..."
3998:589:  ],
3999:590:  "auto_spec_files": [
4000:591:    "${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}/auto-g-auto-001.spec.ts"
4001:592:  ],
4002:593:  "bindings_satisfied": true,
4003:594:  "l1_resolved_count": 0,
4004:595:  "l2_escalations": [
4005:596:    {
4006:597:      "goal_id": "G-XX",
4007:598:      "architect_proposal": "<one-paragraph proposal text>",
4008:599:      "evidence": "<what block-resolver returned>"
4009:600:    }
4010:601:  ],
4011:602:  "binding_failed": false,
4012:603:  "r7_violations": [],
4013:604:  "deferred_goals": ["G-03", "G-07"],
4014:605:  "manual_skeletons": ["G-05"],
4015:606:  "summary": "<one paragraph>",
4016:607:  "warnings": []
4017:608:}
4018:609:```
4019:610:
4020:611:`l2_escalations` MUST be present (empty array if none).
4021:612:`bindings_satisfied` is `true` only if binding gate passed (or L1 resolved it).
4022:613:`binding_failed` is `true` only if L4 stuck (no resolution path found).
4023:614:````
4024:615:
4025:616:---
4026:617:
4027:618:## Allowed tools
4028:619:
4029:620:- Read
4030:621:- Write
4031:622:- Edit
4032:623:- Bash
4033:624:- Glob
4034:625:- Grep
4035:626:
4036:627:`vg-codegen-interactive` skill invocation is allowed (1 call per goal
4037:628:with `interactive_controls.url_sync: true`).
4038:629:
4039:630:---
4040:631:
4041:632:## Forbidden
4042:633:
4043:634:- Spawning sub-subagents (no nested `Agent` calls — no recursive spawn).
4044:635:- Reading TEST-GOALS.md, PLAN.md, or API-CONTRACTS.md via `cat` directly —
4045:636:  goals and contracts are passed via the `goals_index` input field (loaded
4046:637:  by main agent via `vg-load`).
4047:638:- Generating goal verdicts or updating GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md.
4048:639:- Writing any artifact outside `${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}/`, `${PHASE_DIR}/.vg-tmp/`.
4049:640:
4050:641:---
4051:642:
4052:643:## Output (subagent returns)
4053:644:
4054:645:```json
4055:646:{
4056:647:  "spec_files": ["${GENERATED_TESTS_DIR}/${PHASE_NUMBER}-goal-G-01.spec.ts"],
4057:648:  "auto_spec_files": [],
4058:649:  "bindings_satisfied": true,
4059:650:  "l1_resolved_count": 0,
4060:651:  "l2_escalations": [],
4061:652:  "binding_failed": false,
4062:653:  "r7_violations": [],
4063:654:  "deferred_goals": [],
4064:655:  "manual_skeletons": [],
4065:656:  "summary": "Phase N: 8 goals codegenned. 6 READY → full specs, 1 MANUAL skeleton, 1 DEFERRED skipped. Binding gate PASS.",
4066:657:  "warnings": []
4067:658:}
4068:659:```
4069:660:
4070:661:---
4071:662:
4072:663:## Failure modes
4073:664:
4074:665:| Error JSON | Cause | Action |
4075:666:|---|---|---|
4076:667:| `{"error":"missing_input","field":"runtime_map_path"}` | RUNTIME-MAP.json missing | Run /vg:review first |
4077:668:| `{"error":"missing_input","field":"goal_coverage_matrix_path"}` | GOAL-COVERAGE-MATRIX.md missing | Run /vg:review first |
4078:669:| `{"error":"goal_load_failed"}` | vg-load returned empty goals | Run /vg:blueprint first |
4079:670:| `{"error":"dynamic_ids_blocked"}` | Dynamic IDs in goal_sequences, L1 failed | Re-run /vg:review --retry-failed |
4080:671:| `{"error":"binding_failed","l2_escalations":[...]}` | L2 proposals pending | Main agent handles via AskUserQuestion |
4081:672:| `{"error":"r7_violation","specs":[...]}` | Mutation specs missing console assertion | Fix codegen template; re-run |
4082:673:
4083:674:Retry up to 2 times on transient errors, then surface `l2_escalations` to
4084:675:main agent for `AskUserQuestion` (Layer 3). Never retry indefinitely on
4085:676:binding failures — those require code fixes or architect decisions.
