9841:62:<objective>
9842:63:Run the dedicated deep test-spec lane after `/vg:build` and before
9843:64:`/vg:review`.
9844:65:
9845:66:Why this exists:
9846:67:- Blueprint is too early: implemented DOM, route files, API handlers, generated
9847:68:  UI, and concrete form state may not exist yet.
9848:69:- Build must not self-certify runtime coverage.
9849:70:- Review should verify runtime against a pre-authored deep spec contract, not
9850:71:  discover test depth late and route it ambiguously.
9851:72:
9852:73:Pipeline:
9853:74:`specs → scope → blueprint → build → review → test-spec → test → accept`
9854:75:</objective>
9855:76:
9856:77:<rules>
9857:78:1. This command is post-build only. Missing `SUMMARY*.md`, `BUILD-LOG.md`, or
9858:79:   `.build-progress.json` BLOCKs with guidance to run `/vg:build`.
9859:80:2. It authors test-depth contracts, not executable test specs. Executable
9860:81:   specs still belong to `/vg:test`.
9861:82:3. Mutation and multi-actor goals must get closed-loop RCRURDR coverage:
9862:83:   read_before → create → read_after_create → update → read_after_update →
9863:84:   delete → read_after_delete.
9864:85:4. Fixture dependencies must be explicit: actors, sessions, resource ownership,
9865:86:   artifact sinks, cleanup order.
9866:87:5. VG is profile-aware. Web may use Playwright, mobile may use Maestro/Appium/native,
9867:88:   CLI may use command assertions, backend may use HTTP/RPC/job checks, library may
9868:89:   use unit/property tests.
9869:90:6. Review consumes these artifacts. If review finds runtime blockers, stay in
9870:91:   review/debug. If runtime is clean but executable specs are missing, route to
9871:92:   `/vg:test`.
9872:93:</rules>
